54using DelayedInsertionMapKey = std::pair<ParallelMove*, InstructionOperand>;
55
56struct DelayedInsertionMapCompare {
57 bool operator()(const DelayedInsertionMapKey& a,
58 const DelayedInsertionMapKey& b) const {
59 if (a.first == b.first) {
60 return a.second.Compare(b.second);
61 }
62 return a.first < b.first;
63 }
64};

66using DelayedInsertionMap = ZoneMap<DelayedInsertionMapKey, InstructionOperand,
67 DelayedInsertionMapCompare>;

69UsePosition::UsePosition(LifetimePosition pos, InstructionOperand* operand,
70 void* hint, UsePositionHintType hint_type)
71 : operand_(operand), hint_(hint), pos_(pos), flags_(0) {
72 DCHECK_IMPLIES(hint == nullptr, hint_type == UsePositionHintType::kNone);
73 bool register_beneficial = true;
74 UsePositionType type = UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlot;
75 if (operand_ != nullptr && operand_->IsUnallocated()) {
76 const UnallocatedOperand* unalloc = UnallocatedOperand::cast(operand_);
77 if (unalloc->HasRegisterPolicy()) {
78 type = UsePositionType::kRequiresRegister;
79 } else if (unalloc->HasSlotPolicy()) {
80 type = UsePositionType::kRequiresSlot;
81 register_beneficial = false;
82 } else if (unalloc->HasRegisterOrSlotOrConstantPolicy()) {
83 type = UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlotOrConstant;
84 register_beneficial = false;
85 } else {
86 register_beneficial = !unalloc->HasRegisterOrSlotPolicy();
87 }
88 }
89 flags_ = TypeField::encode(type) | HintTypeField::encode(hint_type) |
90 RegisterBeneficialField::encode(register_beneficial) |
91 AssignedRegisterField::encode(kUnassignedRegister);
92 DCHECK(pos_.IsValid());
93}
94
95bool UsePosition::HasHint() const {
96 int hint_register;
97 return HintRegister(&hint_register);
98}

100bool UsePosition::HintRegister(int* register_code) const {
101 if (hint_ == nullptr) return false;
102 switch (HintTypeField::decode(flags_)) {
103 case UsePositionHintType::kNone:
104 case UsePositionHintType::kUnresolved:
105 return false;
106 case UsePositionHintType::kUsePos: {
107 UsePosition* use_pos = reinterpret_cast<UsePosition*>(hint_);
108 int assigned_register = AssignedRegisterField::decode(use_pos->flags_);
109 if (assigned_register == kUnassignedRegister) return false;
110 *register_code = assigned_register;
111 return true;
112 }
113 case UsePositionHintType::kOperand: {
114 InstructionOperand* operand =
115 reinterpret_cast<InstructionOperand*>(hint_);
116 *register_code = LocationOperand::cast(operand)->register_code();
117 return true;
118 }
119 case UsePositionHintType::kPhi: {
120 RegisterAllocationData::PhiMapValue* phi =
121 reinterpret_cast<RegisterAllocationData::PhiMapValue*>(hint_);
122 int assigned_register = phi->assigned_register();
123 if (assigned_register == kUnassignedRegister) return false;
124 *register_code = assigned_register;
125 return true;
126 }
127 }
128 UNREACHABLE();
129}
130
131UsePositionHintType UsePosition::HintTypeForOperand(
132 const InstructionOperand& op) {
133 switch (op.kind()) {
134 case InstructionOperand::CONSTANT:
135 case InstructionOperand::IMMEDIATE:
136 return UsePositionHintType::kNone;
137 case InstructionOperand::UNALLOCATED:
138 return UsePositionHintType::kUnresolved;
139 case InstructionOperand::ALLOCATED:
140 if (op.IsRegister() || op.IsFPRegister()) {
141 return UsePositionHintType::kOperand;
142 } else {
143 DCHECK(op.IsStackSlot() || op.IsFPStackSlot());
144 return UsePositionHintType::kNone;
145 }
146 case InstructionOperand::PENDING:
147 case InstructionOperand::INVALID:
148 break;
149 }
150 UNREACHABLE();
151}

155 hint_ = use_pos;
156 flags_ = HintTypeField::update(flags_, UsePositionHintType::kUsePos);

159void UsePosition::ResolveHint(UsePosition* use_pos) {
160 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(use_pos);
161 if (HintTypeField::decode(flags_) != UsePositionHintType::kUnresolved) return;
162 hint_ = use_pos;
163 flags_ = HintTypeField::update(flags_, UsePositionHintType::kUsePos);

166void UsePosition::set_type(UsePositionType type, bool register_beneficial) {
167 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == UsePositionType::kRequiresSlot, !register_beneficial);
168 DCHECK_EQ(kUnassignedRegister, AssignedRegisterField::decode(flags_));
169 flags_ = TypeField::encode(type) |
170 RegisterBeneficialField::encode(register_beneficial) |
171 HintTypeField::encode(HintTypeField::decode(flags_)) |
172 AssignedRegisterField::encode(kUnassignedRegister);
173}

177LiveRange::LiveRange(int relative_id, MachineRepresentation rep,
178 TopLevelLiveRange* top_level)
179 : relative_id_(relative_id),
180 bits_(0),
181 intervals_(),
182 positions_span_(),
183 top_level_(top_level),
184 next_(nullptr),
185 current_interval_(intervals_.begin()) {
186 DCHECK(AllocatedOperand::IsSupportedRepresentation(rep));
187 bits_ = AssignedRegisterField::encode(kUnassignedRegister) |
188 RepresentationField::encode(rep) |
189 ControlFlowRegisterHint::encode(kUnassignedRegister);

192#ifdef DEBUG
193void LiveRange::VerifyPositions() const {
194 SLOW_DCHECK(std::is_sorted(positions().begin(), positions().end(),
195 UsePosition::Ordering()));
196
197 // Verify that each `UsePosition` is covered by a `UseInterval`.
198 UseIntervalVector::const_iterator interval = intervals().begin();
199 for (UsePosition* pos : positions()) {
200 DCHECK_LE(Start(), pos->pos());
201 DCHECK_LE(pos->pos(), End());
202 DCHECK_NE(interval, intervals().end());
203 // NOTE: Even though `UseInterval`s are conceptually half-open (e.g., when
204 // splitting), we still regard the `UsePosition` that coincides with
205 // the end of an interval as covered by that interval.
206 while (!interval->Contains(pos->pos()) && interval->end() != pos->pos()) {
207 ++interval;
208 DCHECK_NE(interval, intervals().end());
209 }
210 }
211}
212
213void LiveRange::VerifyIntervals() const {
214 DCHECK(!intervals().empty());
215 DCHECK_EQ(intervals().front().start(), Start());
216 // The `UseInterval`s must be sorted and disjoint.
217 LifetimePosition last_end = intervals().front().end();
218 for (UseIntervalVector::const_iterator interval = intervals().begin() + 1;
219 interval != intervals().end(); ++interval) {
220 DCHECK_LE(last_end, interval->start());
221 last_end = interval->end();
222 }
223 DCHECK_EQ(last_end, End());
224}
225#endif

237void LiveRange::AttachToNext(Zone* zone) {
238 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(next_);
239
240 // Update cache for `TopLevelLiveRange::GetChildCovers()`.
241 auto& children = TopLevel()->children_;
242 children.erase(std::lower_bound(children.begin(), children.end(), next_,
243 LiveRangeOrdering()));
244
245 // Merge use intervals.
246 intervals_.Append(zone, next_->intervals_);
247 // `start_` doesn't change.
248 end_ = next_->end_;
249
250 // Merge use positions.
251 CHECK_EQ(positions_span_.end(), next_->positions_span_.begin());
252 positions_span_ =
253 base::VectorOf(positions_span_.begin(),
254 positions_span_.size() + next_->positions_span_.size());
255
256 // Join linked lists of live ranges.
257 LiveRange* old_next = next_;
258 next_ = next_->next_;
259 old_next->next_ = nullptr;
260}

275RegisterKind LiveRange::kind() const {
276 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent &&
277 IsSimd128(representation())) {
278 return RegisterKind::kSimd128;
279 } else {
280 return IsFloatingPoint(representation()) ? RegisterKind::kDouble
281 : RegisterKind::kGeneral;
282 }

285bool LiveRange::RegisterFromFirstHint(int* register_index) {
286 DCHECK_LE(current_hint_position_index_, positions_span_.size());
287 if (current_hint_position_index_ == positions_span_.size()) {
288 return false;
289 }
290 DCHECK_GE(positions_span_[current_hint_position_index_]->pos(),
291 positions_span_.first()->pos());
292 DCHECK_LE(positions_span_[current_hint_position_index_]->pos(), End());
293
294 bool needs_revisit = false;
295 UsePosition** pos_it = positions_span_.begin() + current_hint_position_index_;
296 for (; pos_it != positions_span_.end(); ++pos_it) {
297 if ((*pos_it)->HintRegister(register_index)) {
298 break;
299 }
300 // Phi and use position hints can be assigned during allocation which
301 // would invalidate the cached hint position. Make sure we revisit them.
302 needs_revisit = needs_revisit ||
303 (*pos_it)->hint_type() == UsePositionHintType::kPhi ||
304 (*pos_it)->hint_type() == UsePositionHintType::kUsePos;
305 }
306 if (!needs_revisit) {
307 current_hint_position_index_ =
308 std::distance(positions_span_.begin(), pos_it);
309 }
310#ifdef DEBUG
311 UsePosition** pos_check_it =
312 std::find_if(positions_span_.begin(), positions_span_.end(),
313 [](UsePosition* pos) { return pos->HasHint(); });
314 CHECK_EQ(pos_it, pos_check_it);
315#endif
316 return pos_it != positions_span_.end();
317}

319UsePosition* const* LiveRange::NextUsePosition(LifetimePosition start) const {
320 return std::lower_bound(positions_span_.cbegin(), positions_span_.cend(),
321 start, [](UsePosition* use, LifetimePosition start) {
322 return use->pos() < start;
323 });

326UsePosition* LiveRange::NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(
327 LifetimePosition start) const {
328 UsePosition* const* use_pos_it = std::find_if(
329 NextUsePosition(start), positions_span_.cend(),
330 [](const UsePosition* pos) { return pos->RegisterIsBeneficial(); });
331 return use_pos_it == positions_span_.cend() ? nullptr : *use_pos_it;
332}

334LifetimePosition LiveRange::NextLifetimePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(
335 const LifetimePosition& start) const {
336 UsePosition* next_use = NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(start);
337 if (next_use == nullptr) return End();
338 return next_use->pos();
339}

341UsePosition* LiveRange::NextUsePositionSpillDetrimental(
342 LifetimePosition start) const {
343 UsePosition* const* use_pos_it =
344 std::find_if(NextUsePosition(start), positions_span_.cend(),
345 [](const UsePosition* pos) {
346 return pos->type() == UsePositionType::kRequiresRegister ||
347 pos->SpillDetrimental();
348 });
349 return use_pos_it == positions_span_.cend() ? nullptr : *use_pos_it;
350}

352UsePosition* LiveRange::NextRegisterPosition(LifetimePosition start) const {
353 UsePosition* const* use_pos_it =
354 std::find_if(NextUsePosition(start), positions_span_.cend(),
355 [](const UsePosition* pos) {
356 return pos->type() == UsePositionType::kRequiresRegister;
357 });
358 return use_pos_it == positions_span_.cend() ? nullptr : *use_pos_it;

361bool LiveRange::CanBeSpilled(LifetimePosition pos) const {
362 // We cannot spill a live range that has a use requiring a register
363 // at the current or the immediate next position.
364 UsePosition* use_pos = NextRegisterPosition(pos);
365 if (use_pos == nullptr) return true;
366 return use_pos->pos() > pos.NextStart().End();
367}

371InstructionOperand LiveRange::GetAssignedOperand() const {
372 DCHECK(!IsEmpty());
373 if (HasRegisterAssigned()) {
374 DCHECK(!spilled());
375 return AllocatedOperand(LocationOperand::REGISTER, representation(),
376 assigned_register());
377 }
378 DCHECK(spilled());
379 DCHECK(!HasRegisterAssigned());
380 if (TopLevel()->HasSpillOperand()) {
381 InstructionOperand* op = TopLevel()->GetSpillOperand();
382 DCHECK(!op->IsUnallocated());
383 return *op;
384 }
385 return TopLevel()->GetSpillRangeOperand();
386}

388UseIntervalVector::iterator LiveRange::FirstSearchIntervalForPosition(
389 LifetimePosition position) {
390 DCHECK_NE(current_interval_, intervals_.end());
391 if (current_interval_->start() > position) {
392 current_interval_ = std::lower_bound(
393 intervals_.begin(), intervals_.end(), position,
394 [](const UseInterval& interval, LifetimePosition position) {
395 return interval.end() < position;
396 });
397 }
398 return current_interval_;
399}

401void LiveRange::AdvanceLastProcessedMarker(
402 UseIntervalVector::iterator to_start_of, LifetimePosition but_not_past) {
403 DCHECK_LE(intervals_.begin(), to_start_of);
404 DCHECK_LT(to_start_of, intervals_.end());
405 DCHECK_NE(current_interval_, intervals_.end());
406 if (to_start_of->start() > but_not_past) return;
407 if (to_start_of->start() > current_interval_->start()) {
408 current_interval_ = to_start_of;
409 }
410}

412LiveRange* LiveRange::SplitAt(LifetimePosition position, Zone* zone) {
413 DCHECK(Start() < position);
414 DCHECK(End() > position);
415
416 int new_id = TopLevel()->GetNextChildId();
417 LiveRange* result =
418 zone->New<LiveRange>(new_id, representation(), TopLevel());
419
420 // Partition original use intervals to the two live ranges.
421
422 // Find the first interval that ends after the position. (This either needs
423 // to be split or completely belongs to the split-off LiveRange.)
424 UseIntervalVector::iterator split_interval = std::upper_bound(
425 intervals_.begin(), intervals_.end(), position,
426 [](LifetimePosition position, const UseInterval& interval) {
427 return position < interval.end();
428 });
429 DCHECK_NE(split_interval, intervals_.end());
430
431 bool split_at_start = false;
432 if (split_interval->start() == position) {
433 split_at_start = true;
434 } else if (split_interval->Contains(position)) {
435 UseInterval new_interval = split_interval->SplitAt(position);
436 split_interval = intervals_.insert(zone, split_interval + 1, new_interval);
437 }
438 result->intervals_ = intervals_.SplitAt(split_interval);
439 DCHECK(!intervals_.empty());
440 DCHECK(!result->intervals_.empty());
441
442 result->start_ = result->intervals_.front().start();
443 result->end_ = end_;
444 end_ = intervals_.back().end();
445
446 // Partition use positions.
447 UsePosition** split_position_it;
448 if (split_at_start) {
449 // The split position coincides with the beginning of a use interval
450 // (the end of a lifetime hole). Use at this position should be attributed
451 // to the split child because split child owns use interval covering it.
452 split_position_it = std::lower_bound(
453 positions_span_.begin(), positions_span_.end(), position,
454 [](const UsePosition* use_pos, LifetimePosition pos) {
455 return use_pos->pos() < pos;
456 });
457 } else {
458 split_position_it = std::lower_bound(
459 positions_span_.begin(), positions_span_.end(), position,
460 [](const UsePosition* use_pos, LifetimePosition pos) {
461 return use_pos->pos() <= pos;
462 });
463 }
464
465 size_t result_size = std::distance(split_position_it, positions_span_.end());
466 result->positions_span_ = base::VectorOf(split_position_it, result_size);
467 positions_span_.Truncate(positions_span_.size() - result_size);
468
469 // Update or discard cached iteration state to make sure it does not point
470 // to use positions and intervals that no longer belong to this live range.
471 if (current_hint_position_index_ >= positions_span_.size()) {
472 result->current_hint_position_index_ =
473 current_hint_position_index_ - positions_span_.size();
474 current_hint_position_index_ = 0;
475 }
476
477 current_interval_ = intervals_.begin();
478 result->current_interval_ = result->intervals_.begin();
479
480#ifdef DEBUG
481 VerifyChildStructure();
482 result->VerifyChildStructure();
483#endif
484
485 result->top_level_ = TopLevel();
486 result->next_ = next_;
487 next_ = result;
488
489 // Update cache for `TopLevelLiveRange::GetChildCovers()`.
490 auto& children = TopLevel()->children_;
491 children.insert(std::upper_bound(children.begin(), children.end(), result,
492 LiveRangeOrdering()),
493 1, result);
494 return result;
495}

497void LiveRange::ConvertUsesToOperand(const InstructionOperand& op,
498 const InstructionOperand& spill_op) {
499 for (UsePosition* pos : positions_span_) {
500 DCHECK(Start() <= pos->pos() && pos->pos() <= End());
501 if (!pos->HasOperand()) continue;
502 switch (pos->type()) {
503 case UsePositionType::kRequiresSlot:
504 DCHECK(spill_op.IsStackSlot() || spill_op.IsFPStackSlot());
505 InstructionOperand::ReplaceWith(pos->operand(), &spill_op);
506 break;
507 case UsePositionType::kRequiresRegister:
508 DCHECK(op.IsRegister() || op.IsFPRegister());
509 [[fallthrough]];
510 case UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlot:
511 case UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlotOrConstant:
512 InstructionOperand::ReplaceWith(pos->operand(), &op);
513 break;
514 }
515 }
516}
517
518// This implements an ordering on live ranges so that they are ordered by their
519// start positions. This is needed for the correctness of the register
520// allocation algorithm. If two live ranges start at the same offset then there
521// is a tie breaker based on where the value is first used. This part of the
522// ordering is merely a heuristic.
523bool LiveRange::ShouldBeAllocatedBefore(const LiveRange* other) const {
524 LifetimePosition start = Start();
525 LifetimePosition other_start = other->Start();
526 if (start == other_start) {
527 // Prefer register that has a controlflow hint to make sure it gets
528 // allocated first. This allows the control flow aware alloction to
529 // just put ranges back into the queue without other ranges interfering.
530 if (controlflow_hint() < other->controlflow_hint()) {
531 return true;
532 }
533 // The other has a smaller hint.
534 if (controlflow_hint() > other->controlflow_hint()) {
535 return false;
536 }
537 // Both have the same hint or no hint at all. Use first use position.
538 // To make the order total, handle the case where both positions are null.
539 if (positions_span_.empty() && other->positions_span_.empty()) {
540 return TopLevel()->vreg() < other->TopLevel()->vreg();
541 }
542 if (positions_span_.empty()) return false;
543 if (other->positions_span_.empty()) return true;
544 UsePosition* pos = positions_span_.first();
545 UsePosition* other_pos = other->positions_span_.first();
546 // To make the order total, handle the case where both positions are equal.
547 if (pos->pos() == other_pos->pos())
548 return TopLevel()->vreg() < other->TopLevel()->vreg();
549 return pos->pos() < other_pos->pos();
550 }
551 return start < other_start;
552}
553
554void LiveRange::SetUseHints(int register_index) {
555 for (UsePosition* pos : positions_span_) {
556 if (!pos->HasOperand()) continue;
557 switch (pos->type()) {
558 case UsePositionType::kRequiresSlot:
559 break;
560 case UsePositionType::kRequiresRegister:
561 case UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlot:
562 case UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlotOrConstant:
563 pos->set_assigned_register(register_index);
564 break;
565 }
566 }
567}

569bool LiveRange::CanCover(LifetimePosition position) const {
570 if (IsEmpty()) return false;
571 return Start() <= position && position < End();
572}
573
574bool LiveRange::Covers(LifetimePosition position) {
575 if (!CanCover(position)) return false;
576 bool covers = false;
577 UseIntervalVector::iterator interval =
578 FirstSearchIntervalForPosition(position);
579 while (interval != intervals().end() && interval->start() <= position) {
580 // The list of `UseInterval`s shall be sorted.
581 DCHECK(interval + 1 == intervals().end() ||
582 interval[1].start() >= interval->start());
583 if (interval->Contains(position)) {
584 covers = true;
585 break;
586 }
587 ++interval;
588 }
589 if (!covers && interval > intervals_.begin()) {
590 // To ensure that we advance {current_interval_} below, move back to the
591 // last interval starting before position.
592 interval--;
593 DCHECK_LE(interval->start(), position);
594 }
595 AdvanceLastProcessedMarker(interval, position);
596 return covers;
597}

599LifetimePosition LiveRange::NextEndAfter(LifetimePosition position) {
600 // NOTE: A binary search was measured to be slower, e.g., on the binary from
601 // https://crbug.com/v8/9529.
602 UseIntervalVector::iterator interval = std::find_if(
603 FirstSearchIntervalForPosition(position), intervals_.end(),
604 [=](const UseInterval& interval) { return interval.end() >= position; });
605 DCHECK_NE(interval, intervals().end());
606 return interval->end();
607}

609LifetimePosition LiveRange::NextStartAfter(LifetimePosition position) {
610 // NOTE: A binary search was measured to be slower, e.g., on the binary from
611 // https://crbug.com/v8/9529.
612 UseIntervalVector::iterator interval =
613 std::find_if(FirstSearchIntervalForPosition(position), intervals_.end(),
614 [=](const UseInterval& interval) {
615 return interval.start() >= position;
616 });
617 DCHECK_NE(interval, intervals().end());
618 next_start_ = interval->start();
619 return next_start_;
620}

622LifetimePosition LiveRange::FirstIntersection(LiveRange* other) {
623 if (IsEmpty() || other->IsEmpty() || other->Start() > End() ||
624 Start() > other->End())
625 return LifetimePosition::Invalid();
626
627 LifetimePosition min_end = std::min(End(), other->End());
628 UseIntervalVector::iterator b = other->intervals_.begin();
629 LifetimePosition advance_last_processed_up_to = b->start();
630 UseIntervalVector::iterator a = FirstSearchIntervalForPosition(b->start());
631 while (a != intervals().end() && b != other->intervals().end()) {
632 if (a->start() > min_end || b->start() > min_end) break;
633 LifetimePosition cur_intersection = a->Intersect(*b);
634 if (cur_intersection.IsValid()) {
635 return cur_intersection;
636 }
637 if (a->start() < b->start()) {
638 ++a;
639 if (a == intervals().end() || a->start() > other->End()) break;
640 AdvanceLastProcessedMarker(a, advance_last_processed_up_to);
641 } else {
642 ++b;
643 }
644 }
645 return LifetimePosition::Invalid();
646}

648void LiveRange::Print(const RegisterConfiguration* config,
649 bool with_children) const {
650 StdoutStream os;
651 PrintableLiveRange wrapper;
652 wrapper.register_configuration_ = config;
653 for (const LiveRange* i = this; i != nullptr; i = i->next()) {
654 wrapper.range_ = i;
655 os << wrapper << std::endl;
656 if (!with_children) break;
657 }
658}

671void LiveRange::UpdateBundleRegister(int reg) const {
672 LiveRangeBundle* bundle = TopLevel()->get_bundle();

700void TopLevelLiveRange::RecordSpillLocation(Zone* zone, int gap_index,
701 InstructionOperand* operand) {

703 spill_move_insertion_locations_ = zone->New<SpillMoveInsertionList>(
704 gap_index, operand, spill_move_insertion_locations_);

706
707void TopLevelLiveRange::CommitSpillMoves(RegisterAllocationData* data,
708 const InstructionOperand& op) {
709 DCHECK_IMPLIES(op.IsConstant(),
710 GetSpillMoveInsertionLocations(data) == nullptr);
711
712 if (HasGeneralSpillRange()) {
713 SetLateSpillingSelected(false);
714 }
715
716 InstructionSequence* sequence = data->code();
717 Zone* zone = sequence->zone();
718
719 for (SpillMoveInsertionList* to_spill = GetSpillMoveInsertionLocations(data);
720 to_spill != nullptr; to_spill = to_spill->next) {
721 Instruction* instr = sequence->InstructionAt(to_spill->gap_index);
722 ParallelMove* move =
723 instr->GetOrCreateParallelMove(Instruction::START, zone);
724 move->AddMove(*to_spill->operand, op);
725 instr->block()->mark_needs_frame();
726 }
727}
728
729void TopLevelLiveRange::FilterSpillMoves(RegisterAllocationData* data,
730 const InstructionOperand& op) {
731 DCHECK_IMPLIES(op.IsConstant(),
732 GetSpillMoveInsertionLocations(data) == nullptr);
733 bool might_be_duplicated = has_slot_use() || spilled();
734 InstructionSequence* sequence = data->code();
735
736 SpillMoveInsertionList* previous = nullptr;
737 for (SpillMoveInsertionList* to_spill = GetSpillMoveInsertionLocations(data);
738 to_spill != nullptr; previous = to_spill, to_spill = to_spill->next) {
739 Instruction* instr = sequence->InstructionAt(to_spill->gap_index);
740 ParallelMove* move = instr->GetParallelMove(Instruction::START);
741 // Skip insertion if it's possible that the move exists already as a
742 // constraint move from a fixed output register to a slot.
743 bool found = false;
744 if (move != nullptr && (might_be_duplicated || has_preassigned_slot())) {
745 for (MoveOperands* move_op : *move) {
746 if (move_op->IsEliminated()) continue;
747 if (move_op->source().Equals(*to_spill->operand) &&
748 move_op->destination().Equals(op)) {
749 found = true;
750 if (has_preassigned_slot()) move_op->Eliminate();
751 break;
752 }
753 }
754 }
755 if (found || has_preassigned_slot()) {
756 // Remove the item from the list.
757 if (previous == nullptr) {
758 spill_move_insertion_locations_ = to_spill->next;
759 } else {
760 previous->next = to_spill->next;
761 }
762 // Even though this location doesn't need a spill instruction, the
763 // block does require a frame.
764 instr->block()->mark_needs_frame();
765 }
766 }
767}

788LiveRange* TopLevelLiveRange::GetChildCovers(LifetimePosition pos) {
789#ifdef DEBUG
790 // Make sure the cache contains the correct, actual children.
791 LiveRange* child = this;
792 for (LiveRange* cached_child : children_) {
793 DCHECK_EQ(cached_child, child);
794 child = child->next();
795 }
796 DCHECK_NULL(child);
797#endif
798
799 auto child_it =
800 std::lower_bound(children_.begin(), children_.end(), pos,
801 [](const LiveRange* range, LifetimePosition pos) {
802 return range->End() <= pos;
803 });
804 return child_it == children_.end() || !(*child_it)->Covers(pos) ? nullptr
805 : *child_it;
806}

826void TopLevelLiveRange::ShortenTo(LifetimePosition start) {
827 TRACE("Shorten live range %d to [%d\n", vreg(), start.value());
828 DCHECK(!IsEmpty());
829 DCHECK_LE(intervals_.front().start(), start);
830 intervals_.front().set_start(start);
831 start_ = start;
832}
833
834void TopLevelLiveRange::EnsureInterval(LifetimePosition start,
835 LifetimePosition end, Zone* zone) {
836 TRACE("Ensure live range %d in interval [%d %d[\n", vreg(), start.value(),
837 end.value());
838 DCHECK(!IsEmpty());
839
840 // Drop front intervals until intervals_.front().start() > end.
841 LifetimePosition new_end = end;
842 while (!intervals_.empty() && intervals_.front().start() <= end) {
843 if (intervals_.front().end() > end) {
844 new_end = intervals_.front().end();
845 }
846 intervals_.pop_front();
847 }
848 intervals_.push_front(zone, UseInterval(start, new_end));
849 current_interval_ = intervals_.begin();
850 if (end_ < new_end) {
851 end_ = new_end;
852 }
853 if (start_ > start) {
854 start_ = start;
855 }
856}
857
858void TopLevelLiveRange::AddUseInterval(LifetimePosition start,
859 LifetimePosition end, Zone* zone) {
860 TRACE("Add to live range %d interval [%d %d[\n", vreg(), start.value(),
861 end.value());
862 if (intervals_.empty()) {
863 intervals_.push_front(zone, UseInterval(start, end));
864 start_ = start;
865 end_ = end;
866 } else {
867 UseInterval& first_interval = intervals_.front();
868 if (end == first_interval.start()) {
869 // Coalesce directly adjacent intervals.
870 first_interval.set_start(start);
871 start_ = start;
872 } else if (end < first_interval.start()) {
873 intervals_.push_front(zone, UseInterval(start, end));
874 start_ = start;
875 } else {
876 // Order of instruction's processing (see ProcessInstructions) guarantees
877 // that each new use interval either precedes, intersects with or touches
878 // the last added interval.
879 DCHECK(intervals_.size() == 1 || end <= intervals_.begin()[1].start());
880 first_interval.set_start(std::min(start, first_interval.start()));
881 first_interval.set_end(std::max(end, first_interval.end()));
882 if (start_ > start) {
883 start_ = start;
884 }
885 if (end_ < end) {
886 end_ = end;
887 }
888 }
889 }
890 current_interval_ = intervals_.begin();
891}
892
893void TopLevelLiveRange::AddUsePosition(UsePosition* use_pos, Zone* zone) {
894 TRACE("Add to live range %d use position %d\n", vreg(),
895 use_pos->pos().value());
896 // Since we `ProcessInstructions` in reverse, the `use_pos` is almost always
897 // inserted at the front of `positions_`, hence (i) use linear instead of
898 // binary search and (ii) grow towards the `kFront` exclusively on `insert`.
899 UsePositionVector::iterator insert_it = std::find_if(
900 positions_.begin(), positions_.end(), [=](const UsePosition* pos) {
901 return UsePosition::Ordering()(use_pos, pos);
902 });
903 positions_.insert<kFront>(zone, insert_it, use_pos);
904
905 positions_span_ = base::VectorOf(positions_);
906 // We must not have child `LiveRange`s yet (e.g. from splitting), otherwise we
907 // would have to adjust their `positions_span_` as well.
908 DCHECK_NULL(next_);
909}

935namespace {
936void PrintBlockRow(std::ostream& os, const InstructionBlocks& blocks) {
937 os << " ";
938 for (auto block : blocks) {
939 LifetimePosition start_pos = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
940 block->first_instruction_index());
941 LifetimePosition end_pos = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
942 block->last_instruction_index())
943 .NextFullStart();
944 int length = end_pos.value() - start_pos.value();
945 constexpr int kMaxPrefixLength = 32;
946 char buffer[kMaxPrefixLength];
947 int rpo_number = block->rpo_number().ToInt();
948 const char* deferred_marker = block->IsDeferred() ? "(deferred)" : "";
949 int max_prefix_length = std::min(length, kMaxPrefixLength);
950 int prefix = snprintf(buffer, max_prefix_length, "[-B%d-%s", rpo_number,
951 deferred_marker);
952 os << buffer;
953 int remaining = length - std::min(prefix, max_prefix_length) - 1;
954 for (int i = 0; i < remaining; ++i) os << '-';
955 os << ']';
956 }
957 os << '\n';
958}
959} // namespace
960
961void LinearScanAllocator::PrintRangeRow(std::ostream& os,
962 const TopLevelLiveRange* toplevel) {
963 int position = 0;
964 os << std::setw(3) << toplevel->vreg() << ": ";
965
966 const char* kind_string;
967 switch (toplevel->spill_type()) {
968 case TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType::kSpillRange:
969 kind_string = "ss";
970 break;
971 case TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType::kDeferredSpillRange:
972 kind_string = "sd";
973 break;
974 case TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType::kSpillOperand:
975 kind_string = "so";
976 break;
977 default:
978 kind_string = "s?";
979 }
980
981 for (const LiveRange* range = toplevel; range != nullptr;
982 range = range->next()) {
983 for (const UseInterval& interval : range->intervals()) {
984 LifetimePosition start = interval.start();
985 LifetimePosition end = interval.end();
986 CHECK_GE(start.value(), position);
987 for (; start.value() > position; position++) {
988 os << ' ';
989 }
990 int length = end.value() - start.value();
991 constexpr int kMaxPrefixLength = 32;
992 char buffer[kMaxPrefixLength];
993 int max_prefix_length = std::min(length + 1, kMaxPrefixLength);
994 int prefix;
995 if (range->spilled()) {
996 prefix = snprintf(buffer, max_prefix_length, "|%s", kind_string);
997 } else {
998 prefix = snprintf(buffer, max_prefix_length, "|%s",
999 RegisterName(range->assigned_register()));
1000 }
1001 os << buffer;
1002 position += std::min(prefix, max_prefix_length - 1);
1003 CHECK_GE(end.value(), position);
1004 const char line_style = range->spilled() ? '-' : '=';
1005 for (; end.value() > position; position++) {
1006 os << line_style;
1007 }
1008 }
1009 }
1010 os << '\n';
1011}

1013void LinearScanAllocator::PrintRangeOverview() {
1014 std::ostringstream os;
1015 PrintBlockRow(os, code()->instruction_blocks());
1016 for (auto const toplevel : data()->fixed_live_ranges()) {
1017 if (toplevel == nullptr) continue;
1018 PrintRangeRow(os, toplevel);
1019 }
1020 int rowcount = 0;
1021 for (auto toplevel : data()->live_ranges()) {
1022 if (!CanProcessRange(toplevel)) continue;
1023 if (rowcount++ % 10 == 0) PrintBlockRow(os, code()->instruction_blocks());
1024 PrintRangeRow(os, toplevel);
1025 }
1026 PrintF("%s\n", os.str().c_str());
1027}

1029SpillRange::SpillRange(TopLevelLiveRange* parent, Zone* zone)
1030 : ranges_(zone),
1031 intervals_(zone),
1032 assigned_slot_(kUnassignedSlot),
1033 byte_width_(ByteWidthForStackSlot(parent->representation())) {
1034 DCHECK(!parent->IsEmpty());
1035
1036 // Spill ranges are created for top level. This is so that, when merging
1037 // decisions are made, we consider the full extent of the virtual register,
1038 // and avoid clobbering it.
1039 LifetimePosition last_end = LifetimePosition::MaxPosition();
1040 for (const LiveRange* range = parent; range != nullptr;
1041 range = range->next()) {
1042 // Deep copy the `UseInterval`s, since the `LiveRange`s are subsequently
1043 // modified, so just storing those has correctness issues.
1044 for (UseInterval interval : range->intervals()) {
1045 DCHECK_NE(LifetimePosition::MaxPosition(), interval.start());
1046 bool can_coalesce = last_end == interval.start();
1047 if (can_coalesce) {
1048 intervals_.back().set_end(interval.end());
1049 } else {
1050 intervals_.push_back(interval);
1051 }
1052 last_end = interval.end();
1053 }
1054 }
1055 ranges_.push_back(parent);
1056 parent->SetSpillRange(this);
1057}
1058
1059// Checks if the `UseInterval`s in `a` intersect with those in `b`.
1060// Returns the two intervals that intersected, or `std::nullopt` if none did.
1061static std::optional<std::pair<UseInterval, UseInterval>>
1062AreUseIntervalsIntersectingVector(base::Vector<const UseInterval> a,
1063 base::Vector<const UseInterval> b) {
1064 SLOW_DCHECK(std::is_sorted(a.begin(), a.end()) &&
1065 std::is_sorted(b.begin(), b.end()));
1066 if (a.empty() || b.empty() || a.last().end() <= b.first().start() ||
1067 b.last().end() <= a.first().start()) {
1068 return {};
1069 }
1070
1071 // `a` shall have less intervals then `b`.
1072 if (a.size() > b.size()) {
1073 std::swap(a, b);
1074 }
1075
1076 auto a_it = a.begin();
1077 // Advance `b` already to the interval that ends at or after `a_start`.
1078 LifetimePosition a_start = a.first().start();
1079 auto b_it = std::lower_bound(
1080 b.begin(), b.end(), a_start,
1081 [](const UseInterval& interval, LifetimePosition position) {
1082 return interval.end() < position;
1083 });
1084 while (a_it != a.end() && b_it != b.end()) {
1085 if (a_it->end() <= b_it->start()) {
1086 ++a_it;
1087 } else if (b_it->end() <= a_it->start()) {
1088 ++b_it;
1089 } else {
1090 return std::make_pair(*a_it, *b_it);
1091 }
1092 }
1093 return {};
1094}
1095
1096// Used by `LiveRangeBundle`s and `SpillRange`s, hence allow passing different
1097// containers of `UseInterval`s, as long as they can be converted to a
1098// `base::Vector` (which is essentially just a memory span).
1099template <typename ContainerA, typename ContainerB>
1100std::optional<std::pair<UseInterval, UseInterval>> AreUseIntervalsIntersecting(
1101 const ContainerA& a, const ContainerB& b) {
1102 return AreUseIntervalsIntersectingVector(base::VectorOf(a),
1103 base::VectorOf(b));
1104}
1105
1106bool SpillRange::TryMerge(SpillRange* other) {
1107 if (HasSlot() || other->HasSlot()) return false;
1108 if (byte_width() != other->byte_width()) return false;
1109 if (AreUseIntervalsIntersecting(intervals_, other->intervals_)) return false;
1110
1111 // Merge vectors of `UseInterval`s.
1112 intervals_.reserve(intervals_.size() + other->intervals_.size());
1113 for (UseInterval interval : other->intervals_) {
1114 UseInterval* insert_it =
1115 std::lower_bound(intervals_.begin(), intervals_.end(), interval);
1116 // Since the intervals didn't intersect, they should also be unique.
1117 DCHECK_IMPLIES(insert_it != intervals_.end(), *insert_it != interval);
1118 intervals_.insert(insert_it, 1, interval);
1119 }
1120 other->intervals_.clear();
1121
1122 // Merge vectors of `TopLevelLiveRange`s.
1123 for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : other->ranges_) {
1124 DCHECK(range->GetSpillRange() == other);
1125 range->SetSpillRange(this);
1126 }
1127 ranges_.insert(ranges_.end(), other->ranges_.begin(), other->ranges_.end());
1128 other->ranges_.clear();
1129
1130 return true;
1131}

1208 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1209 fixed_simd128_live_ranges_.resize(
1210 kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister *
1211 this->config()->num_simd128_registers(),

1223 assigned_double_registers_ = code_zone()->New<BitVector>(

1229 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1230 assigned_simd128_registers_ = code_zone()->New<BitVector>(
1231 this->config()->num_simd128_registers(), code_zone());
1232 fixed_simd128_register_use_ = code_zone()->New<BitVector>(
1233 this->config()->num_simd128_registers(), code_zone());
1234 }
1235
1236 this->frame()->SetAllocatedRegisters(assigned_registers_);
1237 this->frame()->SetAllocatedDoubleRegisters(assigned_double_registers_);
1238}

1291bool RegisterAllocationData::ExistsUseWithoutDefinition() {
1292 bool found = false;
1293 for (int operand_index : *live_in_sets()[0]) {
1294 found = true;
1295 PrintF("Register allocator error: live v%d reached first block.\n",
1296 operand_index);
1297 LiveRange* range = GetLiveRangeFor(operand_index);
1298 PrintF(" (first use is at position %d in instruction %d)\n",
1299 range->positions().first()->pos().value(),
1300 range->positions().first()->pos().ToInstructionIndex());
1301 if (debug_name() == nullptr) {
1302 PrintF("\n");
1303 } else {
1304 PrintF(" (function: %s)\n", debug_name());
1305 }
1306 }
1307 return found;
1308}
1309
1310// If a range is defined in a deferred block, we can expect all the range
1311// to only cover positions in deferred blocks. Otherwise, a block on the
1312// hot path would be dominated by a deferred block, meaning it is unreachable
1313// without passing through the deferred block, which is contradictory.
1314// In particular, when such a range contributes a result back on the hot
1315// path, it will be as one of the inputs of a phi. In that case, the value
1316// will be transferred via a move in the Gap::END's of the last instruction
1317// of a deferred block.
1318bool RegisterAllocationData::RangesDefinedInDeferredStayInDeferred() {
1319 const size_t live_ranges_size = live_ranges().size();
1320 for (const TopLevelLiveRange* range : live_ranges()) {
1321 CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
1322 live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
1323 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
1324 if (range->IsEmpty() ||
1325 !code()
1326 ->GetInstructionBlock(range->Start().ToInstructionIndex())
1327 ->IsDeferred()) {
1328 continue;
1329 }
1330 for (const UseInterval& interval : range->intervals()) {
1331 int first = interval.FirstGapIndex();
1332 int last = interval.LastGapIndex();
1333 for (int instr = first; instr <= last;) {
1334 const InstructionBlock* block = code()->GetInstructionBlock(instr);
1335 if (!block->IsDeferred()) return false;
1336 instr = block->last_instruction_index() + 1;
1337 }
1338 }
1339 }
1340 return true;
1341}
1342
1343SpillRange* RegisterAllocationData::AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(
1344 TopLevelLiveRange* range, SpillMode spill_mode) {
1345 using SpillType = TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType;
1346 DCHECK(!range->HasSpillOperand());
1347
1348 SpillRange* spill_range = range->GetAllocatedSpillRange();
1349 if (spill_range == nullptr) {
1350 spill_range = allocation_zone()->New<SpillRange>(range, allocation_zone());
1351 }
1352 if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred &&
1353 (range->spill_type() != SpillType::kSpillRange)) {
1354 range->set_spill_type(SpillType::kDeferredSpillRange);
1355 } else {
1356 range->set_spill_type(SpillType::kSpillRange);
1357 }
1358
1359 return spill_range;
1360}

1362void RegisterAllocationData::MarkFixedUse(MachineRepresentation rep,
1363 int index) {
1364 switch (rep) {
1365 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1366 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1367 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1368 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
1369 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kOverlap) {
1370 fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(index);
1371 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1372 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat16 ||
1373 rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1374 fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(index);
1375 } else {
1376 fixed_simd128_register_use_->Add(index);
1377 }
1378 } else {
1379 int alias_base_index = -1;
1380 int aliases = config()->GetAliases(
1381 rep, index, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, &alias_base_index);
1382 DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
1383 while (aliases--) {
1384 int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
1385 fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(aliased_reg);
1386 }
1387 }
1388 break;
1389 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1390 fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(index);
1391 break;
1392 default:
1393 DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1394 fixed_register_use_->Add(index);
1395 break;
1396 }
1397}
1398
1399bool RegisterAllocationData::HasFixedUse(MachineRepresentation rep, int index) {
1400 switch (rep) {
1401 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1402 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1403 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1404 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256: {
1405 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kOverlap) {
1406 return fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(index);
1407 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1408 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat16 ||
1409 rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1410 return fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(index);
1411 } else {
1412 return fixed_simd128_register_use_->Contains(index);
1413 }
1414 } else {
1415 int alias_base_index = -1;
1416 int aliases = config()->GetAliases(
1417 rep, index, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, &alias_base_index);
1418 DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
1419 bool result = false;
1420 while (aliases-- && !result) {
1421 int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
1422 result |= fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(aliased_reg);
1423 }
1424 return result;
1425 }
1426 }
1427 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1428 return fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(index);
1429 default:
1430 DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1431 return fixed_register_use_->Contains(index);
1432 }
1433}

1435void RegisterAllocationData::MarkAllocated(MachineRepresentation rep,
1436 int index) {
1437 switch (rep) {
1438 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1439 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1440 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1441 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
1442 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kOverlap) {
1443 assigned_double_registers_->Add(index);
1444 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1445 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat16 ||
1446 rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1447 assigned_double_registers_->Add(index);
1448 } else {
1449 assigned_simd128_registers_->Add(index);
1450 }
1451 } else {
1452 int alias_base_index = -1;
1453 int aliases = config()->GetAliases(
1454 rep, index, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, &alias_base_index);
1455 DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
1456 while (aliases--) {
1457 int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
1458 assigned_double_registers_->Add(aliased_reg);
1459 }
1460 }
1461 break;
1462 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1463 assigned_double_registers_->Add(index);
1464 break;
1465 default:
1466 DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1467 assigned_registers_->Add(index);
1468 break;
1469 }

1472bool RegisterAllocationData::IsBlockBoundary(LifetimePosition pos) const {
1473 return pos.IsFullStart() &&
1474 (static_cast<size_t>(pos.ToInstructionIndex()) ==
1475 code()->instructions().size() ||
1476 code()->GetInstructionBlock(pos.ToInstructionIndex())->code_start() ==
1477 pos.ToInstructionIndex());

1480ConstraintBuilder::ConstraintBuilder(RegisterAllocationData* data)
1481 : data_(data) {}
1482
1483InstructionOperand* ConstraintBuilder::AllocateFixed(
1484 UnallocatedOperand* operand, int pos, bool is_tagged, bool is_input) {
1485 TRACE("Allocating fixed reg for op %d\n", operand->virtual_register());
1486 DCHECK(operand->HasFixedPolicy());
1487 InstructionOperand allocated;
1488 MachineRepresentation rep = InstructionSequence::DefaultRepresentation();
1489 int virtual_register = operand->virtual_register();
1490 if (virtual_register != InstructionOperand::kInvalidVirtualRegister) {
1491 rep = data()->RepresentationFor(virtual_register);
1492 }
1493 if (operand->HasFixedSlotPolicy()) {
1494 allocated = AllocatedOperand(AllocatedOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep,
1495 operand->fixed_slot_index());
1496 } else if (operand->HasFixedRegisterPolicy()) {
1497 DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1498 DCHECK(data()->config()->IsAllocatableGeneralCode(
1499 operand->fixed_register_index()));
1500 allocated = AllocatedOperand(AllocatedOperand::REGISTER, rep,
1501 operand->fixed_register_index());
1502 } else if (operand->HasFixedFPRegisterPolicy()) {
1503 DCHECK(IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1504 DCHECK_NE(InstructionOperand::kInvalidVirtualRegister, virtual_register);
1505 allocated = AllocatedOperand(AllocatedOperand::REGISTER, rep,
1506 operand->fixed_register_index());
1507 } else {
1508 UNREACHABLE();
1509 }
1510 if (is_input && allocated.IsAnyRegister()) {
1511 data()->MarkFixedUse(rep, operand->fixed_register_index());
1512 }
1513 InstructionOperand::ReplaceWith(operand, &allocated);
1514 if (is_tagged) {
1515 TRACE("Fixed reg is tagged at %d\n", pos);
1516 Instruction* instr = code()->InstructionAt(pos);
1517 if (instr->HasReferenceMap()) {
1518 instr->reference_map()->RecordReference(*AllocatedOperand::cast(operand));
1519 }
1520 }
1521 return operand;
1522}

1524void ConstraintBuilder::MeetRegisterConstraints() {
1525 for (InstructionBlock* block : code()->instruction_blocks()) {
1526 data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
1527 MeetRegisterConstraints(block);
1528 }
1529}
1530
1531void ConstraintBuilder::MeetRegisterConstraints(const InstructionBlock* block) {
1532 int start = block->first_instruction_index();
1533 int end = block->last_instruction_index();
1534 DCHECK_NE(-1, start);
1535 for (int i = start; i <= end; ++i) {
1536 MeetConstraintsBefore(i);
1537 if (i != end) MeetConstraintsAfter(i);
1538 }
1539 // Meet register constraints for the instruction in the end.
1540 MeetRegisterConstraintsForLastInstructionInBlock(block);
1541}
1542
1543void ConstraintBuilder::MeetRegisterConstraintsForLastInstructionInBlock(
1544 const InstructionBlock* block) {
1545 int end = block->last_instruction_index();
1546 Instruction* last_instruction = code()->InstructionAt(end);
1547 for (size_t i = 0; i < last_instruction->OutputCount(); i++) {
1548 InstructionOperand* output_operand = last_instruction->OutputAt(i);
1549 DCHECK(!output_operand->IsConstant());
1550 UnallocatedOperand* output = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output_operand);
1551 int output_vreg = output->virtual_register();
1552 TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(output_vreg);
1553 bool assigned = false;
1554 if (output->HasFixedPolicy()) {
1555 AllocateFixed(output, -1, false, false);
1556 // This value is produced on the stack, we never need to spill it.
1557 if (output->IsStackSlot()) {
1558 DCHECK(LocationOperand::cast(output)->index() <
1559 data()->frame()->GetSpillSlotCount());
1560 range->SetSpillOperand(LocationOperand::cast(output));
1561 range->SetSpillStartIndex(end);
1562 assigned = true;
1563 }
1564
1565 for (const RpoNumber& succ : block->successors()) {
1566 const InstructionBlock* successor = code()->InstructionBlockAt(succ);
1567 DCHECK_EQ(1, successor->PredecessorCount());
1568 int gap_index = successor->first_instruction_index();
1569 // Create an unconstrained operand for the same virtual register
1570 // and insert a gap move from the fixed output to the operand.
1571 UnallocatedOperand output_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1572 output_vreg);
1573 data()->AddGapMove(gap_index, Instruction::START, *output, output_copy);
1574 }
1575 }
1576
1577 if (!assigned) {
1578 for (const RpoNumber& succ : block->successors()) {
1579 const InstructionBlock* successor = code()->InstructionBlockAt(succ);
1580 DCHECK_EQ(1, successor->PredecessorCount());
1581 int gap_index = successor->first_instruction_index();
1582 range->RecordSpillLocation(allocation_zone(), gap_index, output);
1583 range->SetSpillStartIndex(gap_index);
1584 }
1585 }
1586 }
1587}
1588
1589void ConstraintBuilder::MeetConstraintsAfter(int instr_index) {
1590 Instruction* first = code()->InstructionAt(instr_index);
1591 // Handle fixed temporaries.
1592 for (size_t i = 0; i < first->TempCount(); i++) {
1593 UnallocatedOperand* temp = UnallocatedOperand::cast(first->TempAt(i));
1594 if (temp->HasFixedPolicy()) AllocateFixed(temp, instr_index, false, false);
1595 }
1596 // Handle constant/fixed output operands.
1597 for (size_t i = 0; i < first->OutputCount(); i++) {
1598 InstructionOperand* output = first->OutputAt(i);
1599 if (output->IsConstant()) {
1600 int output_vreg = ConstantOperand::cast(output)->virtual_register();
1601 TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(output_vreg);
1602 range->SetSpillStartIndex(instr_index + 1);
1603 range->SetSpillOperand(output);
1604 continue;
1605 }
1606 UnallocatedOperand* first_output = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output);
1607 TopLevelLiveRange* range =
1608 data()->GetLiveRangeFor(first_output->virtual_register());
1609 bool assigned = false;
1610 if (first_output->HasFixedPolicy()) {
1611 int output_vreg = first_output->virtual_register();
1612 UnallocatedOperand output_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1613 output_vreg);
1614 bool is_tagged = code()->IsReference(output_vreg);
1615 if (first_output->HasSecondaryStorage()) {
1616 range->MarkHasPreassignedSlot();
1617 data()->preassigned_slot_ranges().push_back(
1618 std::make_pair(range, first_output->GetSecondaryStorage()));
1619 }
1620 AllocateFixed(first_output, instr_index, is_tagged, false);
1621
1622 // This value is produced on the stack, we never need to spill it.
1623 if (first_output->IsStackSlot()) {
1624 DCHECK(LocationOperand::cast(first_output)->index() <
1625 data()->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount());
1626 range->SetSpillOperand(LocationOperand::cast(first_output));
1627 range->SetSpillStartIndex(instr_index + 1);
1628 assigned = true;
1629 }
1630 data()->AddGapMove(instr_index + 1, Instruction::START, *first_output,
1631 output_copy);
1632 }
1633 // Make sure we add a gap move for spilling (if we have not done
1634 // so already).
1635 if (!assigned) {
1636 range->RecordSpillLocation(allocation_zone(), instr_index + 1,
1637 first_output);
1638 range->SetSpillStartIndex(instr_index + 1);
1639 }
1640 }
1641}
1642
1643void ConstraintBuilder::MeetConstraintsBefore(int instr_index) {
1644 Instruction* second = code()->InstructionAt(instr_index);
1645 // Handle fixed input operands of second instruction.
1646 ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>* spilled_consts = nullptr;
1647 for (size_t i = 0; i < second->InputCount(); i++) {
1648 InstructionOperand* input = second->InputAt(i);
1649 if (input->IsImmediate()) {
1650 continue; // Ignore immediates.
1651 }
1652 UnallocatedOperand* cur_input = UnallocatedOperand::cast(input);
1653 if (cur_input->HasSlotPolicy()) {
1654 TopLevelLiveRange* range =
1655 data()->GetLiveRangeFor(cur_input->virtual_register());
1656 if (range->HasSpillOperand() && range->GetSpillOperand()->IsConstant()) {
1657 bool already_spilled = false;
1658 if (spilled_consts == nullptr) {
1659 spilled_consts =
1660 allocation_zone()->New<ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>>(
1661 allocation_zone());
1662 } else {
1663 auto it =
1664 std::find(spilled_consts->begin(), spilled_consts->end(), range);
1665 already_spilled = it != spilled_consts->end();
1666 }
1667 auto it = data()->slot_for_const_range().find(range);
1668 if (it == data()->slot_for_const_range().end()) {
1669 DCHECK(!already_spilled);
1670 int width = ByteWidthForStackSlot(range->representation());
1671 int index = data()->frame()->AllocateSpillSlot(width);
1672 auto* slot = AllocatedOperand::New(allocation_zone(),
1673 LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT,
1674 range->representation(), index);
1675 it = data()->slot_for_const_range().emplace(range, slot).first;
1676 }
1677 if (!already_spilled) {
1678 auto* slot = it->second;
1679 int input_vreg = cur_input->virtual_register();
1680 UnallocatedOperand input_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1681 input_vreg);
1682 // Spill at every use position for simplicity, this case is very rare.
1683 data()->AddGapMove(instr_index, Instruction::END, input_copy, *slot);
1684 spilled_consts->push_back(range);
1685 }
1686 }
1687 }
1688 if (cur_input->HasFixedPolicy()) {
1689 int input_vreg = cur_input->virtual_register();
1690 UnallocatedOperand input_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1691 input_vreg);
1692 bool is_tagged = code()->IsReference(input_vreg);
1693 AllocateFixed(cur_input, instr_index, is_tagged, true);
1694 data()->AddGapMove(instr_index, Instruction::END, input_copy, *cur_input);
1695 }
1696 }
1697 // Handle "output same as input" for second instruction.
1698 for (size_t i = 0; i < second->OutputCount(); i++) {
1699 InstructionOperand* output = second->OutputAt(i);
1700 if (!output->IsUnallocated()) continue;
1701 UnallocatedOperand* second_output = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output);
1702 if (!second_output->HasSameAsInputPolicy()) continue;
1703 DCHECK_EQ(0, i); // Only valid for first output.
1704 UnallocatedOperand* cur_input =
1705 UnallocatedOperand::cast(second->InputAt(second_output->input_index()));
1706 int output_vreg = second_output->virtual_register();
1707 int input_vreg = cur_input->virtual_register();
1708 UnallocatedOperand input_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1709 input_vreg);
1710 *cur_input =
1711 UnallocatedOperand(*cur_input, second_output->virtual_register());
1712 MoveOperands* gap_move = data()->AddGapMove(instr_index, Instruction::END,
1713 input_copy, *cur_input);
1714 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(gap_move);
1715 if (code()->IsReference(input_vreg) && !code()->IsReference(output_vreg)) {
1716 if (second->HasReferenceMap()) {
1717 RegisterAllocationData::DelayedReference delayed_reference = {
1718 second->reference_map(), &gap_move->source()};
1719 data()->delayed_references().push_back(delayed_reference);
1720 }
1721 }
1722 }
1723}
1724
1725void ConstraintBuilder::ResolvePhis() {
1726 // Process the blocks in reverse order.
1727 for (InstructionBlock* block : base::Reversed(code()->instruction_blocks())) {
1728 data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
1729 ResolvePhis(block);
1730 }
1731}
1732
1733void ConstraintBuilder::ResolvePhis(const InstructionBlock* block) {
1734 for (PhiInstruction* phi : block->phis()) {
1735 int phi_vreg = phi->virtual_register();
1736 RegisterAllocationData::PhiMapValue* map_value =
1737 data()->InitializePhiMap(block, phi);
1738 InstructionOperand& output = phi->output();
1739 // Map the destination operands, so the commitment phase can find them.
1740 for (size_t i = 0; i < phi->operands().size(); ++i) {
1741 InstructionBlock* cur_block =
1742 code()->InstructionBlockAt(block->predecessors()[i]);
1743 UnallocatedOperand input(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1744 phi->operands()[i]);
1745 MoveOperands* move = data()->AddGapMove(
1746 cur_block->last_instruction_index(), Instruction::END, input, output);
1747 map_value->AddOperand(&move->destination());
1748 DCHECK(!code()
1749 ->InstructionAt(cur_block->last_instruction_index())
1750 ->HasReferenceMap());
1751 }
1752 TopLevelLiveRange* live_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(phi_vreg);
1753 int gap_index = block->first_instruction_index();
1754 live_range->RecordSpillLocation(allocation_zone(), gap_index, &output);
1755 live_range->SetSpillStartIndex(gap_index);
1756 // We use the phi-ness of some nodes in some later heuristics.
1757 live_range->set_is_phi(true);
1758 live_range->set_is_non_loop_phi(!block->IsLoopHeader());
1759 }
1760}
