1762LiveRangeBuilder::LiveRangeBuilder(RegisterAllocationData* data,
1763 Zone* local_zone)
1764 : data_(data), phi_hints_(local_zone) {}
1765
1766SparseBitVector* LiveRangeBuilder::ComputeLiveOut(
1767 const InstructionBlock* block, RegisterAllocationData* data) {
1768 size_t block_index = block->rpo_number().ToSize();
1769 SparseBitVector* live_out = data->live_out_sets()[block_index];
1770 if (live_out == nullptr) {
1771 // Compute live out for the given block, except not including backward
1772 // successor edges.
1773 Zone* zone = data->allocation_zone();
1774 const InstructionSequence* code = data->code();
1775
1776 live_out = zone->New<SparseBitVector>(zone);
1777
1778 // Process all successor blocks.
1779 for (const RpoNumber& succ : block->successors()) {
1780 // Add values live on entry to the successor.
1781 if (succ <= block->rpo_number()) continue;
1782 SparseBitVector* live_in = data->live_in_sets()[succ.ToSize()];
1783 if (live_in != nullptr) live_out->Union(*live_in);
1784
1785 // All phi input operands corresponding to this successor edge are live
1786 // out from this block.
1787 const InstructionBlock* successor = code->InstructionBlockAt(succ);
1788 size_t index = successor->PredecessorIndexOf(block->rpo_number());
1789 DCHECK(index < successor->PredecessorCount());
1790 for (PhiInstruction* phi : successor->phis()) {
1791 live_out->Add(phi->operands()[index]);
1792 }
1793 }
1794 data->live_out_sets()[block_index] = live_out;
1795 }
1796 return live_out;
1797}
1798
1799void LiveRangeBuilder::AddInitialIntervals(const InstructionBlock* block,
1800 SparseBitVector* live_out) {
1801 // Add an interval that includes the entire block to the live range for
1802 // each live_out value.
1803 LifetimePosition start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
1804 block->first_instruction_index());
1805 LifetimePosition end = LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
1806 block->last_instruction_index())
1807 .NextStart();
1808 for (int operand_index : *live_out) {
1809 TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(operand_index);
1810 range->AddUseInterval(start, end, allocation_zone());
1811 }
1812}
1813
1814int LiveRangeBuilder::FixedFPLiveRangeID(int index, MachineRepresentation rep) {
1815 int result = -index - 1;
1816 switch (rep) {
1817 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
1818 result -=
1819 kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_simd128_registers();
1820 [[fallthrough]];
1821 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1822 result -=
1823 kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_float_registers();
1824 [[fallthrough]];
1825 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1826 result -=
1827 kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_double_registers();
1828 [[fallthrough]];
1829 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1830 result -=
1831 kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_general_registers();
1832 break;
1833 default:
1834 UNREACHABLE();
1835 }
1836 return result;
1837}
1838
1839TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::FixedLiveRangeFor(int index,
1840 SpillMode spill_mode) {
1841 int offset = spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition
1842 ? 0
1843 : config()->num_general_registers();
1844 DCHECK(index < config()->num_general_registers());
1845 TopLevelLiveRange* result = data()->fixed_live_ranges()[offset + index];
1846 if (result == nullptr) {
1847 MachineRepresentation rep = InstructionSequence::DefaultRepresentation();
1848 result = data()->NewLiveRange(FixedLiveRangeID(offset + index), rep);
1849 DCHECK(result->IsFixed());
1850 result->set_assigned_register(index);
1851 data()->MarkAllocated(rep, index);
1852 if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
1853 result->set_deferred_fixed();
1854 }
1855 data()->fixed_live_ranges()[offset + index] = result;
1856 }
1857 return result;
1858}
1859
1860TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
1861 int index, MachineRepresentation rep, SpillMode spill_mode) {
1862 int num_regs = config()->num_double_registers();
1863 ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>* live_ranges =
1864 &data()->fixed_double_live_ranges();
1865 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine) {
1866 switch (rep) {
1867 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1868 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1869 num_regs = config()->num_float_registers();
1870 live_ranges = &data()->fixed_float_live_ranges();
1871 break;
1872 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1873 num_regs = config()->num_simd128_registers();
1874 live_ranges = &data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges();
1875 break;
1876 default:
1877 break;
1878 }
1879 }
1880
1881 int offset = spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition ? 0 : num_regs;
1882
1883 DCHECK(index < num_regs);
1884 USE(num_regs);
1885 TopLevelLiveRange* result = (*live_ranges)[offset + index];
1886 if (result == nullptr) {
1887 result = data()->NewLiveRange(FixedFPLiveRangeID(offset + index, rep), rep);
1888 DCHECK(result->IsFixed());
1889 result->set_assigned_register(index);
1890 data()->MarkAllocated(rep, index);
1891 if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
1892 result->set_deferred_fixed();
1893 }
1894 (*live_ranges)[offset + index] = result;
1895 }
1896 return result;
1897}
1898
1899TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::FixedSIMD128LiveRangeFor(
1900 int index, SpillMode spill_mode) {
1901 DCHECK_EQ(kFPAliasing, AliasingKind::kIndependent);
1902 int num_regs = config()->num_simd128_registers();
1903 ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>* live_ranges =
1904 &data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges();
1905 int offset = spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition ? 0 : num_regs;
1906
1907 DCHECK(index < num_regs);
1908 USE(num_regs);
1909 TopLevelLiveRange* result = (*live_ranges)[offset + index];
1910 if (result == nullptr) {
1911 result = data()->NewLiveRange(
1912 FixedFPLiveRangeID(offset + index, MachineRepresentation::kSimd128),
1913 MachineRepresentation::kSimd128);
1914 DCHECK(result->IsFixed());
1915 result->set_assigned_register(index);
1916 data()->MarkAllocated(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, index);
1917 if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
1918 result->set_deferred_fixed();
1919 }
1920 (*live_ranges)[offset + index] = result;
1921 }
1922 return result;
1923}
1924
1925TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::LiveRangeFor(InstructionOperand* operand,
1926 SpillMode spill_mode) {
1927 if (operand->IsUnallocated()) {
1928 return data()->GetLiveRangeFor(
1929 UnallocatedOperand::cast(operand)->virtual_register());
1930 } else if (operand->IsConstant()) {
1931 return data()->GetLiveRangeFor(
1932 ConstantOperand::cast(operand)->virtual_register());
1933 } else if (operand->IsRegister()) {
1934 return FixedLiveRangeFor(
1935 LocationOperand::cast(operand)->GetRegister().code(), spill_mode);
1936 } else if (operand->IsFPRegister()) {
1937 LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(operand);
1938 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent &&
1939 op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
1940 return FixedSIMD128LiveRangeFor(op->register_code(), spill_mode);
1941 }
1942 return FixedFPLiveRangeFor(op->register_code(), op->representation(),
1943 spill_mode);
1944 } else {
1945 return nullptr;
1946 }
1947}
1948
1949UsePosition* LiveRangeBuilder::NewUsePosition(LifetimePosition pos,
1950 InstructionOperand* operand,
1951 void* hint,
1952 UsePositionHintType hint_type) {
1953 return allocation_zone()->New<UsePosition>(pos, operand, hint, hint_type);
1954}
1955
1956UsePosition* LiveRangeBuilder::Define(LifetimePosition position,
1957 InstructionOperand* operand, void* hint,
1958 UsePositionHintType hint_type,
1959 SpillMode spill_mode) {
1960 TopLevelLiveRange* range = LiveRangeFor(operand, spill_mode);
1961 if (range == nullptr) return nullptr;
1962
1963 if (range->IsEmpty() || range->Start() > position) {
1964 // Can happen if there is a definition without use.
1965 range->AddUseInterval(position, position.NextStart(), allocation_zone());
1966 range->AddUsePosition(NewUsePosition(position.NextStart()),
1967 allocation_zone());
1968 } else {
1969 range->ShortenTo(position);
1970 }
1971 if (!operand->IsUnallocated()) return nullptr;
1972 UnallocatedOperand* unalloc_operand = UnallocatedOperand::cast(operand);
1973 UsePosition* use_pos =
1974 NewUsePosition(position, unalloc_operand, hint, hint_type);
1975 range->AddUsePosition(use_pos, allocation_zone());
1976 return use_pos;
1977}
1978
1979UsePosition* LiveRangeBuilder::Use(LifetimePosition block_start,
1980 LifetimePosition position,
1981 InstructionOperand* operand, void* hint,
1982 UsePositionHintType hint_type,
1983 SpillMode spill_mode) {
1984 TopLevelLiveRange* range = LiveRangeFor(operand, spill_mode);
1985 if (range == nullptr) return nullptr;
1986 UsePosition* use_pos = nullptr;
1987 if (operand->IsUnallocated()) {
1988 UnallocatedOperand* unalloc_operand = UnallocatedOperand::cast(operand);
1989 use_pos = NewUsePosition(position, unalloc_operand, hint, hint_type);
1990 range->AddUsePosition(use_pos, allocation_zone());
1991 }
1992 range->AddUseInterval(block_start, position, allocation_zone());
1993 return use_pos;
1994}
1995
1996void LiveRangeBuilder::ProcessInstructions(const InstructionBlock* block,
1997 SparseBitVector* live) {
1998 int block_start = block->first_instruction_index();
1999 LifetimePosition block_start_position =
2000 LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(block_start);
2001 bool fixed_float_live_ranges = false;
2002 bool fixed_simd128_live_ranges = false;
2003 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine) {
2004 int mask = data()->code()->representation_mask();
2005 fixed_float_live_ranges = (mask & kFloat32Bit) != 0;
2006 fixed_simd128_live_ranges = (mask & kSimd128Bit) != 0;
2007 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
2008 int mask = data()->code()->representation_mask();
2009 fixed_simd128_live_ranges = (mask & kSimd128Bit) != 0;
2010 }
2011 SpillMode spill_mode = SpillModeForBlock(block);
2012
2013 for (int index = block->last_instruction_index(); index >= block_start;
2014 index--) {
2015 LifetimePosition curr_position =
2016 LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(index);
2017 Instruction* instr = code()->InstructionAt(index);
2018 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instr);
2019 DCHECK(curr_position.IsInstructionPosition());
2020 // Process output, inputs, and temps of this instruction.
2021 for (size_t i = 0; i < instr->OutputCount(); i++) {
2022 InstructionOperand* output = instr->OutputAt(i);
2023 if (output->IsUnallocated()) {
2024 // Unsupported.
2025 DCHECK(!UnallocatedOperand::cast(output)->HasSlotPolicy());
2026 int out_vreg = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output)->virtual_register();
2027 live->Remove(out_vreg);
2028 } else if (output->IsConstant()) {
2029 int out_vreg = ConstantOperand::cast(output)->virtual_register();
2030 live->Remove(out_vreg);
2031 }
2032 if (block->IsHandler() && index == block_start && output->IsAllocated() &&
2033 output->IsRegister() &&
2034 AllocatedOperand::cast(output)->GetRegister() ==
2035 v8::internal::kReturnRegister0) {
2036 // The register defined here is blocked from gap start - it is the
2037 // exception value.
2038 // TODO(mtrofin): should we explore an explicit opcode for
2039 // the first instruction in the handler?
2040 Define(LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(index), output,
2041 spill_mode);
2042 } else {
2043 Define(curr_position, output, spill_mode);
2044 }
2045 }
2046
2047 if (instr->ClobbersRegisters()) {
2048 for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
2049 // Create a UseInterval at this instruction for all fixed registers,
2050 // (including the instruction outputs). Adding another UseInterval here
2051 // is OK because AddUseInterval will just merge it with the existing
2052 // one at the end of the range.
2053 int code = config()->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
2054 TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedLiveRangeFor(code, spill_mode);
2055 range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2056 allocation_zone());
2057 }
2058 }
2059
2060 if (instr->ClobbersDoubleRegisters()) {
2061 for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_double_registers(); ++i) {
2062 // Add a UseInterval for all DoubleRegisters. See comment above for
2063 // general registers.
2064 int code = config()->GetAllocatableDoubleCode(i);
2065 TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
2066 code, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, spill_mode);
2067 range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2068 allocation_zone());
2069 }
2070 // Clobber fixed float registers on archs with non-simple aliasing.
2071 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine) {
2072 if (fixed_float_live_ranges) {
2073 for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_float_registers();
2074 ++i) {
2075 // Add a UseInterval for all FloatRegisters. See comment above for
2076 // general registers.
2077 int code = config()->GetAllocatableFloatCode(i);
2078 TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
2079 code, MachineRepresentation::kFloat32, spill_mode);
2080 range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2081 allocation_zone());
2082 }
2083 }
2084 if (fixed_simd128_live_ranges) {
2085 for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_simd128_registers();
2086 ++i) {
2087 int code = config()->GetAllocatableSimd128Code(i);
2088 TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
2089 code, MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, spill_mode);
2090 range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2091 allocation_zone());
2092 }
2093 }
2094 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
2095 if (fixed_simd128_live_ranges) {
2096 for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_simd128_registers();
2097 ++i) {
2098 int code = config()->GetAllocatableSimd128Code(i);
2099 TopLevelLiveRange* range =
2100 FixedSIMD128LiveRangeFor(code, spill_mode);
2101 range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2102 allocation_zone());
2103 }
2104 }
2105 }
2106 }
2107
2108 for (size_t i = 0; i < instr->InputCount(); i++) {
2109 InstructionOperand* input = instr->InputAt(i);
2110 if (input->IsImmediate()) {
2111 continue; // Ignore immediates.
2112 }
2113 LifetimePosition use_pos;
2114 if (input->IsUnallocated() &&
2115 UnallocatedOperand::cast(input)->IsUsedAtStart()) {
2116 use_pos = curr_position;
2117 } else {
2118 use_pos = curr_position.End();
2119 }
2120
2121 if (input->IsUnallocated()) {
2122 UnallocatedOperand* unalloc = UnallocatedOperand::cast(input);
2123 int vreg = unalloc->virtual_register();
2124 live->Add(vreg);
2125 if (unalloc->HasSlotPolicy()) {
2126 data()->GetLiveRangeFor(vreg)->register_slot_use(
2127 block->IsDeferred()
2128 ? TopLevelLiveRange::SlotUseKind::kDeferredSlotUse
2129 : TopLevelLiveRange::SlotUseKind::kGeneralSlotUse);
2130 }
2131 }
2132 Use(block_start_position, use_pos, input, spill_mode);
2133 }
2134
2135 for (size_t i = 0; i < instr->TempCount(); i++) {
2136 InstructionOperand* temp = instr->TempAt(i);
2137 // Unsupported.
2138 DCHECK_IMPLIES(temp->IsUnallocated(),
2139 !UnallocatedOperand::cast(temp)->HasSlotPolicy());
2140 if (instr->ClobbersTemps()) {
2141 if (temp->IsRegister()) continue;
2142 if (temp->IsUnallocated()) {
2143 UnallocatedOperand* temp_unalloc = UnallocatedOperand::cast(temp);
2144 if (temp_unalloc->HasFixedPolicy()) {
2145 continue;
2146 }
2147 }
2148 }
2149 Use(block_start_position, curr_position.End(), temp, spill_mode);
2150 Define(curr_position, temp, spill_mode);
2151 }
2152
2153 // Process the moves of the instruction's gaps, making their sources live.
2154 const Instruction::GapPosition kPositions[] = {Instruction::END,
2155 Instruction::START};
2156 curr_position = curr_position.PrevStart();
2157 DCHECK(curr_position.IsGapPosition());
2158 for (const Instruction::GapPosition& position : kPositions) {
2159 ParallelMove* move = instr->GetParallelMove(position);
2160 if (move == nullptr) continue;
2161 if (position == Instruction::END) {
2162 curr_position = curr_position.End();
2163 } else {
2164 curr_position = curr_position.Start();
2165 }
2166 for (MoveOperands* cur : *move) {
2167 InstructionOperand& from = cur->source();
2168 InstructionOperand& to = cur->destination();
2169 void* hint = &to;
2170 UsePositionHintType hint_type = UsePosition::HintTypeForOperand(to);
2171 UsePosition* to_use = nullptr;
2172 int phi_vreg = -1;
2173 if (to.IsUnallocated()) {
2174 int to_vreg = UnallocatedOperand::cast(to).virtual_register();
2175 TopLevelLiveRange* to_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(to_vreg);
2176 if (to_range->is_phi()) {
2177 phi_vreg = to_vreg;
2178 if (to_range->is_non_loop_phi()) {
2179 hint = to_range->current_hint_position();
2180 hint_type = hint == nullptr ? UsePositionHintType::kNone
2181 : UsePositionHintType::kUsePos;
2182 } else {
2183 hint_type = UsePositionHintType::kPhi;
2184 hint = data()->GetPhiMapValueFor(to_vreg);
2185 }
2186 } else {
2187 if (live->Contains(to_vreg)) {
2188 to_use =
2189 Define(curr_position, &to, &from,
2190 UsePosition::HintTypeForOperand(from), spill_mode);
2191 live->Remove(to_vreg);
2192 } else {
2193 cur->Eliminate();
2194 continue;
2195 }
2196 }
2197 } else {
2198 Define(curr_position, &to, spill_mode);
2199 }
2200 UsePosition* from_use = Use(block_start_position, curr_position, &from,
2201 hint, hint_type, spill_mode);
2202 // Mark range live.
2203 if (from.IsUnallocated()) {
2204 live->Add(UnallocatedOperand::cast(from).virtual_register());
2205 }
2206 // When the value is moved to a register to meet input constraints,
2207 // we should consider this value use similar as a register use in the
2208 // backward spilling heuristics, even though this value use is not
2209 // register benefical at the AllocateBlockedReg stage.
2210 if (to.IsAnyRegister() ||
2211 (to.IsUnallocated() &&
2212 UnallocatedOperand::cast(&to)->HasRegisterPolicy())) {
2213 from_use->set_spill_detrimental();
2214 }
2215 // Resolve use position hints just created.
2216 if (to_use != nullptr && from_use != nullptr) {
2217 to_use->ResolveHint(from_use);
2218 from_use->ResolveHint(to_use);
2219 }
2220 DCHECK_IMPLIES(to_use != nullptr, to_use->IsResolved());
2221 DCHECK_IMPLIES(from_use != nullptr, from_use->IsResolved());
2222 // Potentially resolve phi hint.
2223 if (phi_vreg != -1) ResolvePhiHint(&from, from_use);
2224 }
2225 }
2226 }
2227}
2228
2229void LiveRangeBuilder::ProcessPhis(const InstructionBlock* block,
2230 SparseBitVector* live) {
2231 for (PhiInstruction* phi : block->phis()) {
2232 // The live range interval already ends at the first instruction of the
2233 // block.
2234 int phi_vreg = phi->virtual_register();
2235 live->Remove(phi_vreg);
2236 // Select a hint from a predecessor block that precedes this block in the
2237 // rpo order. In order of priority:
2238 // - Avoid hints from deferred blocks.
2239 // - Prefer hints from allocated (or explicit) operands.
2240 // - Prefer hints from empty blocks (containing just parallel moves and a
2241 // jump). In these cases, if we can elide the moves, the jump threader
2242 // is likely to be able to elide the jump.
2243 // The enforcement of hinting in rpo order is required because hint
2244 // resolution that happens later in the compiler pipeline visits
2245 // instructions in reverse rpo order, relying on the fact that phis are
2246 // encountered before their hints.
2247 InstructionOperand* hint = nullptr;
2248 int hint_preference = 0;
2249
2250 // The cost of hinting increases with the number of predecessors. At the
2251 // same time, the typical benefit decreases, since this hinting only
2252 // optimises the execution path through one predecessor. A limit of 2 is
2253 // sufficient to hit the common if/else pattern.
2254 int predecessor_limit = 2;
2255
2256 for (RpoNumber predecessor : block->predecessors()) {
2257 const InstructionBlock* predecessor_block =
2258 code()->InstructionBlockAt(predecessor);
2259 DCHECK_EQ(predecessor_block->rpo_number(), predecessor);
2260
2261 // Only take hints from earlier rpo numbers.
2262 if (predecessor >= block->rpo_number()) continue;
2263
2264 // Look up the predecessor instruction.
2265 const Instruction* predecessor_instr =
2266 GetLastInstruction(code(), predecessor_block);
2267 InstructionOperand* predecessor_hint = nullptr;
2268 // Phis are assigned in the END position of the last instruction in each
2269 // predecessor block.
2270 for (MoveOperands* move :
2271 *predecessor_instr->GetParallelMove(Instruction::END)) {
2272 InstructionOperand& to = move->destination();
2273 if (to.IsUnallocated() &&
2274 UnallocatedOperand::cast(to).virtual_register() == phi_vreg) {
2275 predecessor_hint = &move->source();
2276 break;
2277 }
2278 }
2279 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(predecessor_hint);
2280
2281 // For each predecessor, generate a score according to the priorities
2282 // described above, and pick the best one. Flags in higher-order bits have
2283 // a higher priority than those in lower-order bits.
2284 int predecessor_hint_preference = 0;
2285 const int kNotDeferredBlockPreference = (1 << 2);
2286 const int kMoveIsAllocatedPreference = (1 << 1);
2287 const int kBlockIsEmptyPreference = (1 << 0);
2288
2289 // - Avoid hints from deferred blocks.
2290 if (!predecessor_block->IsDeferred()) {
2291 predecessor_hint_preference |= kNotDeferredBlockPreference;
2292 }
2293
2294 // - Prefer hints from allocated operands.
2295 //
2296 // Already-allocated operands are typically assigned using the parallel
2297 // moves on the last instruction. For example:
2298 //
2299 // gap (v101 = [x0|R|w32]) (v100 = v101)
2300 // ArchJmp
2301 // ...
2302 // phi: v100 = v101 v102
2303 //
2304 // We have already found the END move, so look for a matching START move
2305 // from an allocated operand.
2306 //
2307 // Note that we cannot simply look up data()->live_ranges()[vreg] here
2308 // because the live ranges are still being built when this function is
2309 // called.
2310 // TODO(v8): Find a way to separate hinting from live range analysis in
2311 // BuildLiveRanges so that we can use the O(1) live-range look-up.
2312 auto moves = predecessor_instr->GetParallelMove(Instruction::START);
2313 if (moves != nullptr) {
2314 for (MoveOperands* move : *moves) {
2315 InstructionOperand& to = move->destination();
2316 if (predecessor_hint->Equals(to)) {
2317 if (move->source().IsAllocated()) {
2318 predecessor_hint_preference |= kMoveIsAllocatedPreference;
2319 }
2320 break;
2321 }
2322 }
2323 }
2324
2325 // - Prefer hints from empty blocks.
2326 if (predecessor_block->last_instruction_index() ==
2327 predecessor_block->first_instruction_index()) {
2328 predecessor_hint_preference |= kBlockIsEmptyPreference;
2329 }
2330
2331 if ((hint == nullptr) ||
2332 (predecessor_hint_preference > hint_preference)) {
2333 // Take the hint from this predecessor.
2334 hint = predecessor_hint;
2335 hint_preference = predecessor_hint_preference;
2336 }
2337
2338 if (--predecessor_limit <= 0) break;
2339 }
2340 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(hint);
2341
2342 LifetimePosition block_start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2343 block->first_instruction_index());
2344 UsePosition* use_pos = Define(block_start, &phi->output(), hint,
2345 UsePosition::HintTypeForOperand(*hint),
2346 SpillModeForBlock(block));
2347 MapPhiHint(hint, use_pos);
2348 }
2349}
2350
2351void LiveRangeBuilder::ProcessLoopHeader(const InstructionBlock* block,
2352 SparseBitVector* live) {
2353 DCHECK(block->IsLoopHeader());
2354 // Add a live range stretching from the first loop instruction to the last
2355 // for each value live on entry to the header.
2356 LifetimePosition start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2357 block->first_instruction_index());
2358 LifetimePosition end = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2359 code()->LastLoopInstructionIndex(block))
2360 .NextFullStart();
2361 for (int operand_index : *live) {
2362 TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(operand_index);
2363 range->EnsureInterval(start, end, allocation_zone());
2364 }
2365 // Insert all values into the live in sets of all blocks in the loop.
2366 for (int i = block->rpo_number().ToInt() + 1; i < block->loop_end().ToInt();
2367 ++i) {
2368 live_in_sets()[i]->Union(*live);
2369 }
2370}
2371
2372void LiveRangeBuilder::BuildLiveRanges() {
2373 // Process the blocks in reverse order.
2374 for (int block_id = code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1; block_id >= 0;
2375 --block_id) {
2376 data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
2377 InstructionBlock* block =
2378 code()->InstructionBlockAt(RpoNumber::FromInt(block_id));
2379 SparseBitVector* live = ComputeLiveOut(block, data());
2380 // Initially consider all live_out values live for the entire block. We
2381 // will shorten these intervals if necessary.
2382 AddInitialIntervals(block, live);
2383 // Process the instructions in reverse order, generating and killing
2384 // live values.
2385 ProcessInstructions(block, live);
2386 // All phi output operands are killed by this block.
2387 ProcessPhis(block, live);
2388 // Now live is live_in for this block except not including values live
2389 // out on backward successor edges.
2390 if (block->IsLoopHeader()) ProcessLoopHeader(block, live);
2391 live_in_sets()[block_id] = live;
2392 }
2393 // Postprocess the ranges.
2394 const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
2395 for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
2396 data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
2397 CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
2398 data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
2399 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
2400 // Give slots to all ranges with a non fixed slot use.
2401 if (range->has_slot_use() && range->HasNoSpillType()) {
2402 SpillMode spill_mode =
2403 range->slot_use_kind() ==
2404 TopLevelLiveRange::SlotUseKind::kDeferredSlotUse
2405 ? SpillMode::kSpillDeferred
2406 : SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition;
2407 data()->AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(range, spill_mode);
2408 }
2409 // TODO(bmeurer): This is a horrible hack to make sure that for constant
2410 // live ranges, every use requires the constant to be in a register.
2411 // Without this hack, all uses with "any" policy would get the constant
2412 // operand assigned.
2413 if (range->HasSpillOperand() && range->GetSpillOperand()->IsConstant()) {
2414 for (UsePosition* pos : range->positions()) {
2415 if (pos->type() == UsePositionType::kRequiresSlot ||
2416 pos->type() == UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlotOrConstant) {
2417 continue;
2418 }
2419 UsePositionType new_type = UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlot;
2420 // Can't mark phis as needing a register.
2421 if (!pos->pos().IsGapPosition()) {
2422 new_type = UsePositionType::kRequiresRegister;
2423 }
2424 pos->set_type(new_type, true);
2425 }
2426 }
2427 range->ResetCurrentHintPosition();
2428 }
2429 for (auto preassigned : data()->preassigned_slot_ranges()) {
2430 TopLevelLiveRange* range = preassigned.first;
2431 int slot_id = preassigned.second;
2432 SpillRange* spill = range->HasSpillRange()
2433 ? range->GetSpillRange()
2434 : data()->AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(
2435 range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2436 spill->set_assigned_slot(slot_id);
2437 }
2438#ifdef DEBUG
2439 Verify();
2440#endif
2441}
2442
2443void LiveRangeBuilder::MapPhiHint(InstructionOperand* operand,
2444 UsePosition* use_pos) {
2445 DCHECK(!use_pos->IsResolved());
2446 auto res = phi_hints_.insert(std::make_pair(operand, use_pos));
2447 DCHECK(res.second);
2448 USE(res);
2449}
2450
2451void LiveRangeBuilder::ResolvePhiHint(InstructionOperand* operand,
2452 UsePosition* use_pos) {
2453 auto it = phi_hints_.find(operand);
2454 if (it == phi_hints_.end()) return;
2455 DCHECK(!it->second->IsResolved());
2456 it->second->ResolveHint(use_pos);
2457}
2458
2459#ifdef DEBUG
2460void LiveRangeBuilder::Verify() const {
2461 for (auto& hint : phi_hints_) {
2462 DCHECK(hint.second->IsResolved());
2463 }
2464 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->live_ranges()) {
2465 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current);
2466 if (!current->IsEmpty()) {
2467 // New LiveRanges should not be split.
2468 DCHECK_NULL(current->next());
2469 // General integrity check.
2470 current->Verify();
2471 if (current->intervals().size() < 2) continue;
2472
2473 // Consecutive intervals should not end and start in the same block,
2474 // otherwise the intervals should have been joined, because the
2475 // variable is live throughout that block.
2476 UseIntervalVector::const_iterator interval = current->intervals().begin();
2477 UseIntervalVector::const_iterator next_interval = interval + 1;
2478 DCHECK(NextIntervalStartsInDifferentBlocks(*interval, *next_interval));
2479
2480 for (++interval; interval != current->intervals().end(); ++interval) {
2481 // Except for the first interval, the other intevals must start at
2482 // a block boundary, otherwise data wouldn't flow to them.
2483 // You might trigger this CHECK if your SSA is not valid. For instance,
2484 // if the inputs of a Phi node are in the wrong order.
2485 DCHECK(IntervalStartsAtBlockBoundary(*interval));
2486 // The last instruction of the predecessors of the block the interval
2487 // starts must be covered by the range.
2488 DCHECK(IntervalPredecessorsCoveredByRange(*interval, current));
2489 next_interval = interval + 1;
2490 if (next_interval != current->intervals().end()) {
2491 // Check the consecutive intervals property, except for the last
2492 // interval, where it doesn't apply.
2493 DCHECK(
2494 NextIntervalStartsInDifferentBlocks(*interval, *next_interval));
2495 }
2496 }
2497 }
2498 }
2499}
2500
2501bool LiveRangeBuilder::IntervalStartsAtBlockBoundary(
2502 UseInterval interval) const {
2503 LifetimePosition start = interval.start();
2504 if (!start.IsFullStart()) return false;
2505 int instruction_index = start.ToInstructionIndex();
2506 const InstructionBlock* block =
2507 data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(instruction_index);
2508 return block->first_instruction_index() == instruction_index;
2509}
2510
2511bool LiveRangeBuilder::IntervalPredecessorsCoveredByRange(
2512 UseInterval interval, TopLevelLiveRange* range) const {
2513 LifetimePosition start = interval.start();
2514 int instruction_index = start.ToInstructionIndex();
2515 const InstructionBlock* block =
2516 data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(instruction_index);
2517 for (RpoNumber pred_index : block->predecessors()) {
2518 const InstructionBlock* predecessor =
2519 data()->code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred_index);
2520 LifetimePosition last_pos = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2521 predecessor->last_instruction_index());
2522 last_pos = last_pos.NextStart().End();
2523 if (!range->Covers(last_pos)) return false;
2524 }
2525 return true;
2526}
2527
2528bool LiveRangeBuilder::NextIntervalStartsInDifferentBlocks(
2529 UseInterval interval, UseInterval next) const {
2530 LifetimePosition end = interval.end();
2531 LifetimePosition next_start = next.start();
2532 // Since end is not covered, but the previous position is, move back a
2533 // position
2534 end = end.IsStart() ? end.PrevStart().End() : end.Start();
2535 int last_covered_index = end.ToInstructionIndex();
2536 const InstructionBlock* block =
2537 data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(last_covered_index);
2538 const InstructionBlock* next_block =
2539 data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(next_start.ToInstructionIndex());
2540 return block->rpo_number() < next_block->rpo_number();
2541}
2542#endif
2543
2544void BundleBuilder::BuildBundles() {
2545 TRACE("Build bundles\n");
2546 // Process the blocks in reverse order.
2547 for (int block_id = code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1; block_id >= 0;
2548 --block_id) {
2549 InstructionBlock* block =
2550 code()->InstructionBlockAt(RpoNumber::FromInt(block_id));
2551 TRACE("Block B%d\n", block_id);
2552 for (auto phi : block->phis()) {
2553 TopLevelLiveRange* out_range =
2554 data()->GetLiveRangeFor(phi->virtual_register());
2555 LiveRangeBundle* out = out_range->get_bundle();
2556 if (out == nullptr) {
2557 out = data()->allocation_zone()->New<LiveRangeBundle>(
2558 data()->allocation_zone(), next_bundle_id_++);
2559 out->TryAddRange(out_range);
2560 }
2561 TRACE("Processing phi for v%d with %d:%d\n", phi->virtual_register(),
2562 out_range->TopLevel()->vreg(), out_range->relative_id());
2563 bool phi_interferes_with_backedge_input = false;
2564 for (auto input : phi->operands()) {
2565 TopLevelLiveRange* input_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(input);
2566 TRACE("Input value v%d with range %d:%d\n", input,
2567 input_range->TopLevel()->vreg(), input_range->relative_id());
2568 LiveRangeBundle* input_bundle = input_range->get_bundle();
2569 if (input_bundle != nullptr) {
2570 TRACE("Merge\n");
2571 LiveRangeBundle* merged =
2572 LiveRangeBundle::TryMerge(out, input_bundle);
2573 if (merged != nullptr) {
2574 DCHECK_EQ(out_range->get_bundle(), merged);
2575 DCHECK_EQ(input_range->get_bundle(), merged);
2576 out = merged;
2577 TRACE("Merged %d and %d to %d\n", phi->virtual_register(), input,
2578 out->id());
2579 } else if (input_range->Start() > out_range->Start()) {
2580 // We are only interested in values defined after the phi, because
2581 // those are values that will go over a back-edge.
2582 phi_interferes_with_backedge_input = true;
2583 }
2584 } else {
2585 TRACE("Add\n");
2586 if (out->TryAddRange(input_range)) {
2587 TRACE("Added %d and %d to %d\n", phi->virtual_register(), input,
2588 out->id());
2589 } else if (input_range->Start() > out_range->Start()) {
2590 // We are only interested in values defined after the phi, because
2591 // those are values that will go over a back-edge.
2592 phi_interferes_with_backedge_input = true;
2593 }
2594 }
2595 }
2596 // Spilling the phi at the loop header is not beneficial if there is
2597 // a back-edge with an input for the phi that interferes with the phi's
2598 // value, because in case that input gets spilled it might introduce
2599 // a stack-to-stack move at the back-edge.
2600 if (phi_interferes_with_backedge_input)
2601 out_range->TopLevel()->set_spilling_at_loop_header_not_beneficial();
2602 }
2603 TRACE("Done block B%d\n", block_id);
2604 }
2605}
2606
2607bool LiveRangeBundle::TryAddRange(TopLevelLiveRange* range) {
2608 DCHECK_NULL(range->get_bundle());
2609 // We may only add a new live range if its use intervals do not
2610 // overlap with existing intervals in the bundle.
2611 if (AreUseIntervalsIntersecting(this->intervals_, range->intervals()))
2612 return false;
2613 AddRange(range);
2614 return true;
2615}
2616
2617void LiveRangeBundle::AddRange(TopLevelLiveRange* range) {
2618 TopLevelLiveRange** range_insert_it = std::lower_bound(
2619 ranges_.begin(), ranges_.end(), range, LiveRangeOrdering());
2620 DCHECK_IMPLIES(range_insert_it != ranges_.end(), *range_insert_it != range);
2621 // TODO(dlehmann): We might save some memory by using
2622 // `DoubleEndedSplitVector::insert<kFront>()` here: Since we add ranges
2623 // mostly backwards, ranges with an earlier `Start()` are inserted mostly
2624 // at the front.
2625 ranges_.insert(range_insert_it, 1, range);
2626 range->set_bundle(this);
2627
2628 // We also tried `std::merge`ing the sorted vectors of `intervals_` directly,
2629 // but it turns out the (always happening) copies are more expensive
2630 // than the (apparently seldom) copies due to insertion in the middle.
2631 for (UseInterval interval : range->intervals()) {
2632 UseInterval* interval_insert_it =
2633 std::lower_bound(intervals_.begin(), intervals_.end(), interval);
2634 DCHECK_IMPLIES(interval_insert_it != intervals_.end(),
2635 *interval_insert_it != interval);
2636 intervals_.insert(interval_insert_it, 1, interval);
2637 }
2638}
2639
2640LiveRangeBundle* LiveRangeBundle::TryMerge(LiveRangeBundle* lhs,
2641 LiveRangeBundle* rhs) {
2642 if (rhs == lhs) return lhs;
2643
2644 if (auto found =
2645 AreUseIntervalsIntersecting(lhs->intervals_, rhs->intervals_)) {
2646 auto [interval1, interval2] = *found;
2647 TRACE("No merge %d:%d %d:%d\n", interval1.start().value(),
2648 interval1.end().value(), interval2.start().value(),
2649 interval2.end().value());
2650 return nullptr;
2651 }
2652 // Uses are disjoint, merging is possible.
2653
2654 // Merge the smaller bundle into the bigger.
2655 if (lhs->intervals_.size() < rhs->intervals_.size()) {
2656 std::swap(lhs, rhs);
2657 }
2658 for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : rhs->ranges_) {
2659 lhs->AddRange(range);
2660 }
2661
2662 rhs->ranges_.clear();
2663 rhs->intervals_.clear();
2664
2665 return lhs;
2666}
2667
2668void LiveRangeBundle::MergeSpillRangesAndClear() {
2669 DCHECK_IMPLIES(ranges_.empty(), intervals_.empty());
2670 SpillRange* target = nullptr;
2671 for (auto range : ranges_) {
2672 if (range->TopLevel()->HasSpillRange()) {
2673 SpillRange* current = range->TopLevel()->GetSpillRange();
2674 if (target == nullptr) {
2675 target = current;
2676 } else if (target != current) {
2677 target->TryMerge(current);
2678 }
2679 }
2680 }
2681 // Clear the fields so that we don't try to merge the spill ranges again when
2682 // we hit the same bundle from a different LiveRange in AssignSpillSlots.
2683 // LiveRangeBundles are not used after this.
2684 ranges_.clear();
2685 intervals_.clear();
2686}

2704LifetimePosition RegisterAllocator::GetSplitPositionForInstruction(
2705 const LiveRange* range, int instruction_index) {
2706 LifetimePosition ret = LifetimePosition::Invalid();
2707
2708 ret = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(instruction_index);
2709 if (range->Start() >= ret || ret >= range->End()) {
2710 return LifetimePosition::Invalid();
2711 }

2714
2715void RegisterAllocator::SplitAndSpillRangesDefinedByMemoryOperand() {
2716 size_t initial_range_count = data()->live_ranges().size();
2717 for (size_t i = 0; i < initial_range_count; ++i) {
2718 CHECK_EQ(initial_range_count,
2719 data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
2720 TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->live_ranges()[i];
2721 if (!CanProcessRange(range)) continue;
2722 // Only assume defined by memory operand if we are guaranteed to spill it or
2723 // it has a spill operand.
2724 if (range->HasNoSpillType() ||
2725 (range->HasSpillRange() && !range->has_non_deferred_slot_use())) {
2726 continue;
2727 }
2728 LifetimePosition start = range->Start();
2729 TRACE("Live range %d:%d is defined by a spill operand.\n",
2730 range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
2731 LifetimePosition next_pos = start;
2732 if (next_pos.IsGapPosition()) {
2733 next_pos = next_pos.NextStart();
2734 }
2735
2736 UsePosition* pos = range->NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(next_pos);
2737 // If the range already has a spill operand and it doesn't need a
2738 // register immediately, split it and spill the first part of the range.
2739 if (pos == nullptr) {
2740 Spill(range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2741 } else if (pos->pos() > range->Start().NextStart()) {
2742 // Do not spill live range eagerly if use position that can benefit from
2743 // the register is too close to the start of live range.
2744 LifetimePosition split_pos = GetSplitPositionForInstruction(
2745 range, pos->pos().ToInstructionIndex());
2746 // There is no place to split, so we can't split and spill.
2747 if (!split_pos.IsValid()) continue;
2748
2749 split_pos =
2750 FindOptimalSplitPos(range->Start().NextFullStart(), split_pos);
2751
2752 SplitRangeAt(range, split_pos);
2753 Spill(range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2754 }
2755 }
2756}
2757
2758LiveRange* RegisterAllocator::SplitRangeAt(LiveRange* range,
2759 LifetimePosition pos) {
2760 DCHECK(!range->TopLevel()->IsFixed());
2761 TRACE("Splitting live range %d:%d at %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
2762 range->relative_id(), pos.value());
2763
2764 if (pos <= range->Start()) return range;
2765
2766 // We can't properly connect liveranges if splitting occurred at the end
2767 // a block.
2768 DCHECK(pos.IsStart() || pos.IsGapPosition() ||
2769 (GetInstructionBlock(code(), pos)->last_instruction_index() !=
2770 pos.ToInstructionIndex()));
2771
2772 LiveRange* result = range->SplitAt(pos, allocation_zone());
2773 return result;
2774}
2775
2776LiveRange* RegisterAllocator::SplitBetween(LiveRange* range,
2777 LifetimePosition start,
2778 LifetimePosition end) {
2779 DCHECK(!range->TopLevel()->IsFixed());
2780 TRACE("Splitting live range %d:%d in position between [%d, %d]\n",
2781 range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id(), start.value(),
2782 end.value());
2783
2784 LifetimePosition split_pos = FindOptimalSplitPos(start, end);
2785 DCHECK(split_pos >= start);
2786 return SplitRangeAt(range, split_pos);
2787}
2788
2789LifetimePosition RegisterAllocator::FindOptimalSplitPos(LifetimePosition start,
2790 LifetimePosition end) {
2791 int start_instr = start.ToInstructionIndex();
2792 int end_instr = end.ToInstructionIndex();
2793 DCHECK_LE(start_instr, end_instr);
2794
2795 // We have no choice
2796 if (start_instr == end_instr) return end;
2797
2798 const InstructionBlock* start_block = GetInstructionBlock(code(), start);
2799 const InstructionBlock* end_block = GetInstructionBlock(code(), end);
2800
2801 if (end_block == start_block) {
2802 // The interval is split in the same basic block. Split at the latest
2803 // possible position.
2804 return end;
2805 }
2806
2807 const InstructionBlock* block = end_block;
2808 // Find header of outermost loop.
2809 do {
2810 const InstructionBlock* loop = GetContainingLoop(code(), block);
2811 if (loop == nullptr ||
2812 loop->rpo_number().ToInt() <= start_block->rpo_number().ToInt()) {
2813 // No more loops or loop starts before the lifetime start.
2814 break;
2815 }
2816 block = loop;
2817 } while (true);
2818
2819 // We did not find any suitable outer loop. Split at the latest possible
2820 // position unless end_block is a loop header itself.
2821 if (block == end_block && !end_block->IsLoopHeader()) return end;
2822
2823 return LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2824 block->first_instruction_index());
2825}
2826
2827LifetimePosition RegisterAllocator::FindOptimalSpillingPos(
2828 LiveRange* range, LifetimePosition pos, SpillMode spill_mode,
2829 LiveRange** begin_spill_out) {
2830 *begin_spill_out = range;
2831 // TODO(herhut): Be more clever here as long as we do not move pos out of
2832 // deferred code.
2833 if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) return pos;
2834 const InstructionBlock* block = GetInstructionBlock(code(), pos.Start());
2835 const InstructionBlock* loop_header =
2836 block->IsLoopHeader() ? block : GetContainingLoop(code(), block);
2837 if (loop_header == nullptr) return pos;
2838
2839 while (loop_header != nullptr) {
2840 // We are going to spill live range inside the loop.
2841 // If possible try to move spilling position backwards to loop header.
2842 // This will reduce number of memory moves on the back edge.
2843 LifetimePosition loop_start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2844 loop_header->first_instruction_index());
2845 // Stop if we moved to a loop header before the value is defined or
2846 // at the define position that is not beneficial to spill.
2847 if (range->TopLevel()->Start() > loop_start ||
2848 (range->TopLevel()->Start() == loop_start &&
2849 range->TopLevel()->SpillAtLoopHeaderNotBeneficial()))
2850 return pos;
2851
2852 LiveRange* live_at_header = range->TopLevel()->GetChildCovers(loop_start);
2853
2854 if (live_at_header != nullptr && !live_at_header->spilled()) {
2855 for (const LiveRange* check_use = live_at_header;
2856 check_use != nullptr && check_use->Start() < pos;
2857 check_use = check_use->next()) {
2858 // If we find a use for which spilling is detrimental, don't spill
2859 // at the loop header
2860 UsePosition* next_use =
2861 check_use->NextUsePositionSpillDetrimental(loop_start);
2862 // UsePosition at the end of a UseInterval may
2863 // have the same value as the start of next range.
2864 if (next_use != nullptr && next_use->pos() <= pos) {
2865 return pos;
2866 }
2867 }
2868 // No register beneficial use inside the loop before the pos.
2869 *begin_spill_out = live_at_header;
2870 pos = loop_start;
2871 }
2872
2873 // Try hoisting out to an outer loop.
2874 loop_header = GetContainingLoop(code(), loop_header);
2875 }
2876 return pos;
2877}
2878
2879void RegisterAllocator::Spill(LiveRange* range, SpillMode spill_mode) {
2880 DCHECK(!range->spilled());
2881 DCHECK(spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition ||
2882 GetInstructionBlock(code(), range->Start())->IsDeferred());
2883 TopLevelLiveRange* first = range->TopLevel();
2884 TRACE("Spilling live range %d:%d mode %d\n", first->vreg(),
2885 range->relative_id(), spill_mode);
2886
2887 TRACE("Starting spill type is %d\n", static_cast<int>(first->spill_type()));
2888 if (first->HasNoSpillType()) {
2889 TRACE("New spill range needed\n");
2890 data()->AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(first, spill_mode);
2891 }
2892 // Upgrade the spillmode, in case this was only spilled in deferred code so
2893 // far.
2894 if ((spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition) &&
2895 (first->spill_type() ==
2896 TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType::kDeferredSpillRange)) {
2897 TRACE("Upgrading\n");
2898 first->set_spill_type(TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType::kSpillRange);
2899 }
2900 TRACE("Final spill type is %d\n", static_cast<int>(first->spill_type()));
2901 range->Spill();
2902}

2906 switch (mode()) {

2909 case RegisterKind::kDouble:

2928void LinearScanAllocator::MaybeSpillPreviousRanges(LiveRange* begin_range,
2929 LifetimePosition begin_pos,
2930 LiveRange* end_range) {
2931 // Spill begin_range after begin_pos, then spill every live range of this
2932 // virtual register until but excluding end_range.
2933 DCHECK(begin_range->Covers(begin_pos));
2934 DCHECK_EQ(begin_range->TopLevel(), end_range->TopLevel());
2935
2936 if (begin_range != end_range) {
2937 DCHECK_LE(begin_range->End(), end_range->Start());
2938 if (!begin_range->spilled()) {
2939 SpillAfter(begin_range, begin_pos, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2940 }
2941 for (LiveRange* range = begin_range->next(); range != end_range;
2942 range = range->next()) {
2943 if (!range->spilled()) {
2944 range->Spill();
2945 }
2946 }
2947 }
2948}
2949
2950void LinearScanAllocator::MaybeUndoPreviousSplit(LiveRange* range, Zone* zone) {
2951 if (range->next() != nullptr && range->next()->ShouldRecombine()) {
2952 LiveRange* to_remove = range->next();
2953 TRACE("Recombining %d:%d with %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
2954 range->relative_id(), to_remove->relative_id());
2955
2956 // Remove the range from unhandled, as attaching it will change its
2957 // state and hence ordering in the unhandled set.
2958 auto removed_cnt = unhandled_live_ranges().erase(to_remove);
2959 DCHECK_EQ(removed_cnt, 1);
2960 USE(removed_cnt);
2961
2962 range->AttachToNext(zone);
2963 } else if (range->next() != nullptr) {
2964 TRACE("No recombine for %d:%d to %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
2965 range->relative_id(), range->next()->relative_id());
2966 }
2967}
2968
2969void LinearScanAllocator::SpillNotLiveRanges(RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live,
2970 LifetimePosition position,
2971 SpillMode spill_mode) {
2972 for (auto it = active_live_ranges().begin();
2973 it != active_live_ranges().end();) {
2974 LiveRange* active_range = *it;
2975 TopLevelLiveRange* toplevel = (*it)->TopLevel();
2976 auto found = to_be_live.find(toplevel);
2977 if (found == to_be_live.end()) {
2978 // Is not contained in {to_be_live}, spill it.
2979 // Fixed registers are exempt from this. They might have been
2980 // added from inactive at the block boundary but we know that
2981 // they cannot conflict as they are built before register
2982 // allocation starts. It would be algorithmically fine to split
2983 // them and reschedule but the code does not allow to do this.
2984 if (toplevel->IsFixed()) {
2985 TRACE("Keeping reactivated fixed range for %s\n",
2986 RegisterName(toplevel->assigned_register()));
2987 ++it;
2988 } else {
2989 // When spilling a previously spilled/reloaded range, we add back the
2990 // tail that we might have split off when we reloaded/spilled it
2991 // previously. Otherwise we might keep generating small split-offs.
2992 MaybeUndoPreviousSplit(active_range, allocation_zone());
2993 TRACE("Putting back %d:%d\n", toplevel->vreg(),
2994 active_range->relative_id());
2995 LiveRange* split = SplitRangeAt(active_range, position);
2996 DCHECK_NE(split, active_range);
2997
2998 // Make sure we revisit this range once it has a use that requires
2999 // a register.
3000 UsePosition* next_use = split->NextRegisterPosition(position);
3001 if (next_use != nullptr) {
3002 // Move to the start of the gap before use so that we have a space
3003 // to perform the potential reload. Otherwise, do not spill but add
3004 // to unhandled for reallocation.
3005 LifetimePosition revisit_at = next_use->pos().FullStart();
3006 TRACE("Next use at %d\n", revisit_at.value());
3007 if (!data()->IsBlockBoundary(revisit_at)) {
3008 // Leave some space so we have enough gap room.
3009 revisit_at = revisit_at.PrevStart().FullStart();
3010 }
3011 // If this range became life right at the block boundary that we are
3012 // currently processing, we do not need to split it. Instead move it
3013 // to unhandled right away.
3014 if (position < revisit_at) {
3015 LiveRange* third_part = SplitRangeAt(split, revisit_at);
3016 DCHECK_NE(split, third_part);
3017 Spill(split, spill_mode);
3018 TRACE("Marking %d:%d to recombine\n", toplevel->vreg(),
3019 third_part->relative_id());
3020 third_part->SetRecombine();
3021 AddToUnhandled(third_part);
3022 } else {
3023 AddToUnhandled(split);
3024 }
3025 } else {
3026 Spill(split, spill_mode);
3027 }
3028 it = ActiveToHandled(it);
3029 }
3030 } else {
3031 // This range is contained in {to_be_live}, so we can keep it.
3032 int expected_register = found->second;
3033 to_be_live.erase(found);
3034 if (expected_register == active_range->assigned_register()) {
3035 // Was life and in correct register, simply pass through.
3036 TRACE("Keeping %d:%d in %s\n", toplevel->vreg(),
3037 active_range->relative_id(),
3038 RegisterName(active_range->assigned_register()));
3039 ++it;
3040 } else {
3041 // Was life but wrong register. Split and schedule for
3042 // allocation.
3043 TRACE("Scheduling %d:%d\n", toplevel->vreg(),
3044 active_range->relative_id());
3045 LiveRange* split = SplitRangeAt(active_range, position);
3046 split->set_controlflow_hint(expected_register);
3047 AddToUnhandled(split);
3048 it = ActiveToHandled(it);
3049 }
3050 }
3051 }
3052}
3053
3054LiveRange* LinearScanAllocator::AssignRegisterOnReload(LiveRange* range,
3055 int reg) {
3056 // We know the register is currently free but it might be in
3057 // use by a currently inactive range. So we might not be able
3058 // to reload for the full distance. In such case, split here.
3059 // TODO(herhut):
3060 // It might be better if we could use the normal unhandled queue and
3061 // give reloading registers pecedence. That way we would compute the
3062 // intersection for the entire future.
3063 LifetimePosition new_end = range->End();
3064 for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_registers(); ++cur_reg) {
3065 if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) &&
3066 cur_reg != reg) {
3067 continue;
3068 }
3069 SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
3070 for (LiveRange* cur_inactive : inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg)) {
3071 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing() &&
3072 !data()->config()->AreAliases(cur_inactive->representation(), cur_reg,
3073 range->representation(), reg)) {
3074 continue;
3075 }
3076 if (new_end <= cur_inactive->NextStart()) {
3077 // Inactive ranges are sorted by their next start, so the remaining
3078 // ranges cannot contribute to new_end.
3079 break;
3080 }
3081 auto next_intersection = cur_inactive->FirstIntersection(range);
3082 if (!next_intersection.IsValid()) continue;
3083 new_end = std::min(new_end, next_intersection);
3084 }
3085 }
3086 if (new_end != range->End()) {
3087 TRACE("Found new end for %d:%d at %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3088 range->relative_id(), new_end.value());
3089 LiveRange* tail = SplitRangeAt(range, new_end);
3090 AddToUnhandled(tail);
3091 }
3092 SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(range, reg);
3093 return range;
3094}
3095
3096void LinearScanAllocator::ReloadLiveRanges(
3097 RangeRegisterSmallMap const& to_be_live, LifetimePosition position) {
3098 // Assumption: All ranges in {to_be_live} are currently spilled and there are
3099 // no conflicting registers in the active ranges.
3100 // The former is ensured by SpillNotLiveRanges, the latter is by construction
3101 // of the to_be_live set.
3102 for (auto [range, reg] : to_be_live) {
3103 LiveRange* to_resurrect = range->GetChildCovers(position);
3104 if (to_resurrect == nullptr) {
3105 // While the range was life until the end of the predecessor block, it is
3106 // not live in this block. Either there is a lifetime gap or the range
3107 // died.
3108 TRACE("No candidate for %d at %d\n", range->vreg(), position.value());
3109 } else {
3110 // We might be resurrecting a range that we spilled until its next use
3111 // before. In such cases, we have to unsplit it before processing as
3112 // otherwise we might get register changes from one range to the other
3113 // in the middle of blocks.
3114 // If there is a gap between this range and the next, we can just keep
3115 // it as a register change won't hurt.
3116 MaybeUndoPreviousSplit(to_resurrect, allocation_zone());
3117 if (to_resurrect->Start() == position) {
3118 // This range already starts at this block. It might have been spilled,
3119 // so we have to unspill it. Otherwise, it is already in the unhandled
3120 // queue waiting for processing.
3121 DCHECK(!to_resurrect->HasRegisterAssigned());
3122 TRACE("Reload %d:%d starting at %d itself\n", range->vreg(),
3123 to_resurrect->relative_id(), position.value());
3124 if (to_resurrect->spilled()) {
3125 to_resurrect->Unspill();
3126 to_resurrect->set_controlflow_hint(reg);
3127 AddToUnhandled(to_resurrect);
3128 } else {
3129 // Assign the preassigned register if we know. Otherwise, nothing to
3130 // do as already in unhandeled.
3131 if (reg != kUnassignedRegister) {
3132 auto erased_cnt = unhandled_live_ranges().erase(to_resurrect);
3133 DCHECK_EQ(erased_cnt, 1);
3134 USE(erased_cnt);
3135 // We know that there is no conflict with active ranges, so just
3136 // assign the register to the range.
3137 to_resurrect = AssignRegisterOnReload(to_resurrect, reg);
3138 AddToActive(to_resurrect);
3139 }
3140 }
3141 } else {
3142 // This range was spilled before. We have to split it and schedule the
3143 // second part for allocation (or assign the register if we know).
3144 DCHECK(to_resurrect->spilled());
3145 LiveRange* split = SplitRangeAt(to_resurrect, position);
3146 TRACE("Reload %d:%d starting at %d as %d\n", range->vreg(),
3147 to_resurrect->relative_id(), split->Start().value(),
3148 split->relative_id());
3149 DCHECK_NE(split, to_resurrect);
3150 if (reg != kUnassignedRegister) {
3151 // We know that there is no conflict with active ranges, so just
3152 // assign the register to the range.
3153 split = AssignRegisterOnReload(split, reg);
3154 AddToActive(split);
3155 } else {
3156 // Let normal register assignment find a suitable register.
3157 split->set_controlflow_hint(reg);
3158 AddToUnhandled(split);
3159 }
3160 }
3161 }
3162 }
3163}
3164
3165RpoNumber LinearScanAllocator::ChooseOneOfTwoPredecessorStates(
3166 InstructionBlock* current_block, LifetimePosition boundary) {
3167 // Pick the state that would generate the least spill/reloads.
3168 // Compute vectors of ranges with use counts for both sides.
3169 // We count uses only for live ranges that are unique to either the left or
3170 // the right predecessor since many live ranges are shared between both.
3171 // Shared ranges don't influence the decision anyway and this is faster.
3172 auto& left = data()->GetSpillState(current_block->predecessors()[0]);
3173 auto& right = data()->GetSpillState(current_block->predecessors()[1]);
3174
3175 // Build a set of the `TopLevelLiveRange`s in the left predecessor.
3176 // Usually this set is very small, e.g., for JetStream2 at most 3 ranges in
3177 // ~72% of the cases and at most 8 ranges in ~93% of the cases. In those cases
3178 // `SmallMap` is backed by inline storage and uses fast linear search.
3179 // In some pathological cases the set grows large (e.g. the Wasm binary of
3180 // v8:9529) and then `SmallMap` gives us O(log n) worst case lookup when
3181 // intersecting with the right predecessor below. The set is encoded as a
3182 // `SmallMap` to `Dummy` values, since we don't have an equivalent `SmallSet`.
3183 struct Dummy {};
3184 SmallZoneMap<TopLevelLiveRange*, Dummy, 16> left_set(allocation_zone());
3185 for (LiveRange* range : left) {
3186 TopLevelLiveRange* parent = range->TopLevel();
3187 auto [_, inserted] = left_set.emplace(parent, Dummy{});
3188 // The `LiveRange`s in `left` come from the spill state, which is just the
3189 // list of active `LiveRange`s at the end of the block (see
3190 // `RememberSpillState`). Since at most one `LiveRange` out of a
3191 // `TopLevelLiveRange` can be active at the same time, there should never be
3192 // the same `TopLevelLiveRange` twice in `left_set`, hence this check.
3193 DCHECK(inserted);
3194 USE(inserted);
3195 }
3196
3197 // Now build a list of ranges unique to either the left or right predecessor.
3198 struct RangeUseCount {
3199 // The set above contains `TopLevelLiveRange`s, but ultimately we want to
3200 // count uses of the child `LiveRange` covering `boundary`.
3201 // The lookup in `GetChildCovers` is O(log n), so do it only once when
3202 // inserting into this list.
3203 LiveRange* range;
3204 // +1 if used in the left predecessor, -1 if used in the right predecessor.
3205 int use_count_delta;
3206 };
3207 SmallZoneVector<RangeUseCount, 16> unique_range_use_counts(allocation_zone());
3208 for (LiveRange* range : right) {
3209 TopLevelLiveRange* parent = range->TopLevel();
3210 auto left_it = left_set.find(parent);
3211 bool range_is_shared_left_and_right = left_it != left_set.end();
3212 if (range_is_shared_left_and_right) {
3213 left_set.erase(left_it);
3214 } else {
3215 // This range is unique to the right predecessor, so insert into the list.
3216 LiveRange* child = parent->GetChildCovers(boundary);
3217 if (child != nullptr) {
3218 unique_range_use_counts.push_back({child, -1});
3219 }
3220 }
3221 }
3222 // So far `unique_range_use_counts` contains only the ranges unique in the
3223 // right predecessor. Now also add the ranges from the left predecessor.
3224 for (auto [parent, _] : left_set) {
3225 LiveRange* child = parent->GetChildCovers(boundary);
3226 if (child != nullptr) {
3227 unique_range_use_counts.push_back({child, +1});
3228 }
3229 }
3230
3231 // Finally, count the uses for each range.
3232 int use_count_difference = 0;
3233 for (auto [range, use_count] : unique_range_use_counts) {
3234 if (range->NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(boundary) != nullptr) {
3235 use_count_difference += use_count;
3236 }
3237 }
3238 if (use_count_difference == 0) {
3239 // There is a tie in beneficial register uses. Now, look at any use at all.
3240 // We do not account for all uses, like flowing into a phi.
3241 // So we just look at ranges still being live.
3242 TRACE("Looking at only uses\n");
3243 for (auto [range, use_count] : unique_range_use_counts) {
3244 if (range->NextUsePosition(boundary) != range->positions().end()) {
3245 use_count_difference += use_count;
3246 }
3247 }
3248 }
3249 TRACE("Left predecessor has %d more uses than right\n", use_count_difference);
3250 return use_count_difference > 0 ? current_block->predecessors()[0]
3251 : current_block->predecessors()[1];
3252}
3253
3254bool LinearScanAllocator::CheckConflict(
3255 MachineRepresentation rep, int reg,
3256 const RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live) {
3257 for (auto [range, expected_reg] : to_be_live) {
3258 if (data()->config()->AreAliases(range->representation(), expected_reg, rep,
3259 reg)) {
3260 return true;
3261 }
3262 }
3263 return false;
3264}
3265
3266void LinearScanAllocator::ComputeStateFromManyPredecessors(
3267 InstructionBlock* current_block, RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live) {
3268 struct Vote {
3269 size_t count;
3270 int used_registers[RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters];
3271 explicit Vote(int reg) : count(1), used_registers{0} {
3272 used_registers[reg] = 1;
3273 }
3274 };
3275 struct TopLevelLiveRangeComparator {
3276 bool operator()(const TopLevelLiveRange* lhs,
3277 const TopLevelLiveRange* rhs) const {
3278 return lhs->vreg() < rhs->vreg();
3279 }
3280 };
3281 // Typically this map is very small, e.g., on JetStream2 it has at most 3
3282 // elements ~80% of the time and at most 8 elements ~94% of the time.
3283 // Thus use a `SmallZoneMap` to avoid allocations and because linear search
3284 // in an array is faster than map lookup for such small sizes.
3285 // We don't want too many inline elements though since `Vote` is pretty large.
3286 using RangeVoteMap =
3287 SmallZoneMap<TopLevelLiveRange*, Vote, 16, TopLevelLiveRangeComparator>;
3288 static_assert(sizeof(RangeVoteMap) < 4096, "too large stack allocation");
3289 RangeVoteMap counts(data()->allocation_zone());
3290
3291 int deferred_blocks = 0;
3292 for (RpoNumber pred : current_block->predecessors()) {
3293 if (!ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(current_block, pred)) {
3294 // Back edges of a loop count as deferred here too.
3295 deferred_blocks++;
3296 continue;
3297 }
3298 const auto& pred_state = data()->GetSpillState(pred);
3299 for (LiveRange* range : pred_state) {
3300 // We might have spilled the register backwards, so the range we
3301 // stored might have lost its register. Ignore those.
3302 if (!range->HasRegisterAssigned()) continue;
3303 TopLevelLiveRange* toplevel = range->TopLevel();
3304 auto [it, inserted] =
3305 counts.try_emplace(toplevel, range->assigned_register());
3306 if (!inserted) {
3307 it->second.count++;
3308 it->second.used_registers[range->assigned_register()]++;
3309 }
3310 }
3311 }
3312
3313 // Choose the live ranges from the majority.
3314 const size_t majority =
3315 (current_block->PredecessorCount() + 2 - deferred_blocks) / 2;
3316 bool taken_registers[RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters] = {false};
3317 DCHECK(to_be_live.empty());
3318 auto assign_to_live = [this, majority, &counts](
3319 std::function<bool(TopLevelLiveRange*)> filter,
3320 RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live,
3321 bool* taken_registers) {
3322 bool check_aliasing =
3323 kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing();
3324 for (const auto& val : counts) {
3325 if (!filter(val.first)) continue;
3326 if (val.second.count >= majority) {
3327 int register_max = 0;
3328 int reg = kUnassignedRegister;
3329 bool conflict = false;
3330 int num_regs = num_registers();
3331 int num_codes = num_allocatable_registers();
3332 const int* codes = allocatable_register_codes();
3333 MachineRepresentation rep = val.first->representation();
3334 if (check_aliasing && (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32 ||
3335 rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128 ||
3336 rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd256))
3337 GetFPRegisterSet(rep, &num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
3338 for (int idx = 0; idx < num_regs; idx++) {
3339 int uses = val.second.used_registers[idx];
3340 if (uses == 0) continue;
3341 if (uses > register_max || (conflict && uses == register_max)) {
3342 reg = idx;
3343 register_max = uses;
3344 conflict = check_aliasing ? CheckConflict(rep, reg, to_be_live)
3345 : taken_registers[reg];
3346 }
3347 }
3348 if (conflict) {
3349 reg = kUnassignedRegister;
3350 } else if (!check_aliasing) {
3351 taken_registers[reg] = true;
3352 }
3353 TRACE("Reset %d as live due vote %zu in %s\n", val.first->vreg(),
3354 val.second.count, RegisterName(reg));
3355 auto [_, inserted] = to_be_live.emplace(val.first, reg);
3356 DCHECK(inserted);
3357 USE(inserted);
3358 }
3359 }
3360 };
3361 // First round, process fixed registers, as these have precedence.
3362 // There is only one fixed range per register, so we cannot have
3363 // conflicts.
3364 assign_to_live([](TopLevelLiveRange* r) { return r->IsFixed(); }, to_be_live,
3365 taken_registers);
3366 // Second round, process the rest.
3367 assign_to_live([](TopLevelLiveRange* r) { return !r->IsFixed(); }, to_be_live,
3368 taken_registers);
3369}
3370
3371bool LinearScanAllocator::ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(
3372 InstructionBlock* current_block, RpoNumber predecessor) {
3373 // We ignore predecessors on back edges when looking for control flow effects,
3374 // as those lie in the future of allocation and we have no data yet. Also,
3375 // deferred bocks are ignored on deferred to non-deferred boundaries, as we do
3376 // not want them to influence allocation of non deferred code.
3377 return (predecessor < current_block->rpo_number()) &&
3378 (current_block->IsDeferred() ||
3379 !code()->InstructionBlockAt(predecessor)->IsDeferred());
3380}
3381
3382void LinearScanAllocator::UpdateDeferredFixedRanges(SpillMode spill_mode,
3383 InstructionBlock* block) {
3384 if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
3385 LifetimePosition max = LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
3386 LastDeferredInstructionIndex(block));
3387 // Adds range back to inactive, resolving resulting conflicts.
3388 auto add_to_inactive = [this, max](LiveRange* range) {
3389 AddToInactive(range);
3390 // Splits other if it conflicts with range. Other is placed in unhandled
3391 // for later reallocation.
3392 auto split_conflicting = [this, max](LiveRange* range, LiveRange* other,
3393 std::function<void(LiveRange*)>
3394 update_caches) {
3395 if (other->TopLevel()->IsFixed()) return;
3396 int reg = range->assigned_register();
3397 if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
3398 if (other->assigned_register() != reg) {
3399 return;
3400 }
3401 } else {
3402 if (!data()->config()->AreAliases(range->representation(), reg,
3403 other->representation(),
3404 other->assigned_register())) {
3405 return;
3406 }
3407 }
3408 // The inactive range might conflict, so check whether we need to
3409 // split and spill. We can look for the first intersection, as there
3410 // cannot be any intersections in the past, as those would have been a
3411 // conflict then.
3412 LifetimePosition next_start = range->FirstIntersection(other);
3413 if (!next_start.IsValid() || (next_start > max)) {
3414 // There is no conflict or the conflict is outside of the current
3415 // stretch of deferred code. In either case we can ignore the
3416 // inactive range.
3417 return;
3418 }
3419 // They overlap. So we need to split active and reschedule it
3420 // for allocation.
3421 TRACE("Resolving conflict of %d with deferred fixed for register %s\n",
3422 other->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3423 RegisterName(other->assigned_register()));
3424 LiveRange* split_off =
3425 other->SplitAt(next_start, data()->allocation_zone());
3426 // Try to get the same register after the deferred block.
3427 split_off->set_controlflow_hint(other->assigned_register());
3428 DCHECK_NE(split_off, other);
3429 AddToUnhandled(split_off);
3430 update_caches(other);
3431 };
3432 // Now check for conflicts in active and inactive ranges. We might have
3433 // conflicts in inactive, as we do not do this check on every block
3434 // boundary but only on deferred/non-deferred changes but inactive
3435 // live ranges might become live on any block boundary.
3436 for (auto active : active_live_ranges()) {
3437 split_conflicting(range, active, [this](LiveRange* updated) {
3438 next_active_ranges_change_ =
3439 std::min(updated->End(), next_active_ranges_change_);
3440 });
3441 }
3442 for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3443 if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) &&
3444 reg != range->assigned_register()) {
3445 continue;
3446 }
3447 SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(reg);
3448 for (auto inactive : inactive_live_ranges(reg)) {
3449 if (inactive->NextStart() > max) break;
3450 split_conflicting(range, inactive, [this](LiveRange* updated) {
3451 next_inactive_ranges_change_ =
3452 std::min(updated->End(), next_inactive_ranges_change_);
3453 });
3454 }
3455 }
3456 };
3457 if (mode() == RegisterKind::kGeneral) {
3458 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_live_ranges()) {
3459 if (current != nullptr) {
3460 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3461 add_to_inactive(current);
3462 }
3463 }
3464 }
3465 } else if (mode() == RegisterKind::kDouble) {
3466 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_double_live_ranges()) {
3467 if (current != nullptr) {
3468 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3469 add_to_inactive(current);
3470 }
3471 }
3472 }
3473 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing()) {
3474 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_float_live_ranges()) {
3475 if (current != nullptr) {
3476 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3477 add_to_inactive(current);
3478 }
3479 }
3480 }
3481 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3482 if (current != nullptr) {
3483 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3484 add_to_inactive(current);
3485 }
3486 }
3487 }
3488 }
3489 } else {
3490 DCHECK_EQ(mode(), RegisterKind::kSimd128);
3491 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3492 if (current != nullptr) {
3493 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3494 add_to_inactive(current);
3495 }
3496 }
3497 }
3498 }
3499 } else {
3500 // Remove all ranges.
3501 for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3502 for (auto it = inactive_live_ranges(reg).begin();
3503 it != inactive_live_ranges(reg).end();) {
3504 if ((*it)->TopLevel()->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3505 it = inactive_live_ranges(reg).erase(it);
3506 } else {
3507 ++it;
3508 }
3509 }
3510 }
3511 }
3512}

3514bool LinearScanAllocator::BlockIsDeferredOrImmediatePredecessorIsNotDeferred(
3515 const InstructionBlock* block) {
3516 if (block->IsDeferred()) return true;
3517 if (block->PredecessorCount() == 0) return true;
3518 bool pred_is_deferred = false;
3519 for (auto pred : block->predecessors()) {
3520 if (pred.IsNext(block->rpo_number())) {
3521 pred_is_deferred = code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred)->IsDeferred();
3522 break;
3523 }
3524 }
3525 return !pred_is_deferred;
3526}

3529 for (auto pred : block->predecessors()) {

3531 if (!pred_block->IsDeferred()) return true;
3532 }
