3535
3536void LinearScanAllocator::AllocateRegisters() {
3537 DCHECK(unhandled_live_ranges().empty());
3538 DCHECK(active_live_ranges().empty());
3539 for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3540 DCHECK(inactive_live_ranges(reg).empty());
3541 }
3542
3543 SplitAndSpillRangesDefinedByMemoryOperand();
3544 data()->ResetSpillState();
3545
3546 if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_alloc) {
3547 PrintRangeOverview();
3548 }
3549
3550 const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
3551 for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
3552 CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
3553 data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
3554 if (!CanProcessRange(range)) continue;
3555 for (LiveRange* to_add = range; to_add != nullptr;
3556 to_add = to_add->next()) {
3557 if (!to_add->spilled()) {
3558 AddToUnhandled(to_add);
3559 }
3560 }
3561 }
3562
3563 if (mode() == RegisterKind::kGeneral) {
3564 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_live_ranges()) {
3565 if (current != nullptr) {
3566 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3567 AddToInactive(current);
3568 }
3569 }
3570 } else if (mode() == RegisterKind::kDouble) {
3571 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_double_live_ranges()) {
3572 if (current != nullptr) {
3573 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3574 AddToInactive(current);
3575 }
3576 }
3577 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing()) {
3578 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_float_live_ranges()) {
3579 if (current != nullptr) {
3580 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3581 AddToInactive(current);
3582 }
3583 }
3584 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3585 if (current != nullptr) {
3586 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3587 AddToInactive(current);
3588 }
3589 }
3590 }
3591 } else {
3592 DCHECK(mode() == RegisterKind::kSimd128);
3593 for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3594 if (current != nullptr) {
3595 if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3596 AddToInactive(current);
3597 }
3598 }
3599 }
3600
3601 RpoNumber last_block = RpoNumber::FromInt(0);
3602 RpoNumber max_blocks =
3603 RpoNumber::FromInt(code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1);
3604 LifetimePosition next_block_boundary =
3605 LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
3606 data()
3607 ->code()
3608 ->InstructionBlockAt(last_block)
3609 ->last_instruction_index())
3610 .NextFullStart();
3611 SpillMode spill_mode = SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition;
3612
3613 // Process all ranges. We also need to ensure that we have seen all block
3614 // boundaries. Linear scan might have assigned and spilled ranges before
3615 // reaching the last block and hence we would ignore control flow effects for
3616 // those. Not only does this produce a potentially bad assignment, it also
3617 // breaks with the invariant that we undo spills that happen in deferred code
3618 // when crossing a deferred/non-deferred boundary.
3619 while (!unhandled_live_ranges().empty() || last_block < max_blocks) {
3620 data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
3621 LiveRange* current = unhandled_live_ranges().empty()
3622 ? nullptr
3623 : *unhandled_live_ranges().begin();
3624 LifetimePosition position =
3625 current ? current->Start() : next_block_boundary;
3626#ifdef DEBUG
3627 allocation_finger_ = position;
3628#endif
3629 // Check whether we just moved across a block boundary. This will trigger
3630 // for the first range that is past the current boundary.
3631 if (position >= next_block_boundary) {
3632 TRACE("Processing boundary at %d leaving %d\n",
3633 next_block_boundary.value(), last_block.ToInt());
3634
3635 // Forward state to before block boundary
3636 LifetimePosition end_of_block = next_block_boundary.PrevStart().End();
3637 ForwardStateTo(end_of_block);
3638
3639 // Remember this state.
3640 InstructionBlock* current_block = data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(
3641 next_block_boundary.ToInstructionIndex());
3642
3643 // Store current spill state (as the state at end of block). For
3644 // simplicity, we store the active ranges, e.g., the live ranges that
3645 // are not spilled.
3646 data()->RememberSpillState(last_block, active_live_ranges());
3647
3648 // Only reset the state if this was not a direct fallthrough. Otherwise
3649 // control flow resolution will get confused (it does not expect changes
3650 // across fallthrough edges.).
3651 bool fallthrough =
3652 (current_block->PredecessorCount() == 1) &&
3653 current_block->predecessors()[0].IsNext(current_block->rpo_number());
3654
3655 // When crossing a deferred/non-deferred boundary, we have to load or
3656 // remove the deferred fixed ranges from inactive.
3657 if ((spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) !=
3658 current_block->IsDeferred()) {
3659 // Update spill mode.
3660 spill_mode = current_block->IsDeferred()
3661 ? SpillMode::kSpillDeferred
3662 : SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition;
3663
3664 ForwardStateTo(next_block_boundary);
3665
3666#ifdef DEBUG
3667 // Allow allocation at current position.
3668 allocation_finger_ = next_block_boundary;
3669#endif
3670 UpdateDeferredFixedRanges(spill_mode, current_block);
3671 }
3672
3673 // Allocation relies on the fact that each non-deferred block has at
3674 // least one non-deferred predecessor. Check this invariant here.
3675 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!current_block->IsDeferred(),
3676 HasNonDeferredPredecessor(current_block));
3677
3678 if (!fallthrough) {
3679#ifdef DEBUG
3680 // Allow allocation at current position.
3681 allocation_finger_ = next_block_boundary;
3682#endif
3683
3684 // We are currently at next_block_boundary - 1. Move the state to the
3685 // actual block boundary position. In particular, we have to
3686 // reactivate inactive ranges so that they get rescheduled for
3687 // allocation if they were not live at the predecessors.
3688 ForwardStateTo(next_block_boundary);
3689
3690 RangeRegisterSmallMap to_be_live(allocation_zone());
3691
3692 // If we end up deciding to use the state of the immediate
3693 // predecessor, it is better not to perform a change. It would lead to
3694 // the same outcome anyway.
3695 // This may never happen on boundaries between deferred and
3696 // non-deferred code, as we rely on explicit respill to ensure we
3697 // spill at definition.
3698 bool no_change_required = false;
3699
3700 auto pick_state_from = [this, current_block](
3701 RpoNumber pred,
3702 RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live) -> bool {
3703 TRACE("Using information from B%d\n", pred.ToInt());
3704 // If this is a fall-through that is not across a deferred
3705 // boundary, there is nothing to do.
3706 bool is_noop = pred.IsNext(current_block->rpo_number());
3707 if (!is_noop) {
3708 auto& spill_state = data()->GetSpillState(pred);
3709 TRACE("Not a fallthrough. Adding %zu elements...\n",
3710 spill_state.size());
3711 LifetimePosition pred_end =
3712 LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
3713 this->code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred)->code_end());
3714 DCHECK(to_be_live.empty());
3715 for (const auto range : spill_state) {
3716 // Filter out ranges that were split or had their register
3717 // stolen by backwards working spill heuristics. These have
3718 // been spilled after the fact, so ignore them.
3719 if (range->End() < pred_end || !range->HasRegisterAssigned())
3720 continue;
3721 auto [_, inserted] = to_be_live.emplace(
3722 range->TopLevel(), range->assigned_register());
3723 DCHECK(inserted);
3724 USE(inserted);
3725 }
3726 }
3727 return is_noop;
3728 };
3729
3730 // Multiple cases here:
3731 // 1) We have a single predecessor => this is a control flow split, so
3732 // just restore the predecessor state.
3733 // 2) We have two predecessors => this is a conditional, so break ties
3734 // based on what to do based on forward uses, trying to benefit
3735 // the same branch if in doubt (make one path fast).
3736 // 3) We have many predecessors => this is a switch. Compute union
3737 // based on majority, break ties by looking forward.
3738 if (current_block->PredecessorCount() == 1) {
3739 TRACE("Single predecessor for B%d\n",
3740 current_block->rpo_number().ToInt());
3741 no_change_required =
3742 pick_state_from(current_block->predecessors()[0], to_be_live);
3743 } else if (current_block->PredecessorCount() == 2) {
3744 TRACE("Two predecessors for B%d\n",
3745 current_block->rpo_number().ToInt());
3746 // If one of the branches does not contribute any information,
3747 // e.g. because it is deferred or a back edge, we can short cut
3748 // here right away.
3749 RpoNumber chosen_predecessor = RpoNumber::Invalid();
3750 if (!ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(current_block,
3751 current_block->predecessors()[0])) {
3752 chosen_predecessor = current_block->predecessors()[1];
3753 } else if (!ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(
3754 current_block, current_block->predecessors()[1])) {
3755 chosen_predecessor = current_block->predecessors()[0];
3756 } else {
3757 chosen_predecessor = ChooseOneOfTwoPredecessorStates(
3758 current_block, next_block_boundary);
3759 }
3760 no_change_required = pick_state_from(chosen_predecessor, to_be_live);
3761
3762 } else {
3763 // Merge at the end of, e.g., a switch.
3764 ComputeStateFromManyPredecessors(current_block, to_be_live);
3765 }
3766
3767 if (!no_change_required) {
3768 SpillNotLiveRanges(to_be_live, next_block_boundary, spill_mode);
3769 ReloadLiveRanges(to_be_live, next_block_boundary);
3770 }
3771 }
3772 // Update block information
3773 last_block = current_block->rpo_number();
3774 next_block_boundary = LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
3775 current_block->last_instruction_index())
3776 .NextFullStart();
3777
3778 // We might have created new unhandled live ranges, so cycle around the
3779 // loop to make sure we pick the top most range in unhandled for
3780 // processing.
3781 continue;
3782 }
3783
3784 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current);
3785
3786 TRACE("Processing interval %d:%d start=%d\n", current->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3787 current->relative_id(), position.value());
3788
3789 // Now we can erase current, as we are sure to process it.
3790 unhandled_live_ranges().erase(unhandled_live_ranges().begin());
3791
3792 if (current->IsTopLevel() && TryReuseSpillForPhi(current->TopLevel()))
3793 continue;
3794
3795 ForwardStateTo(position);
3796
3797 DCHECK(!current->HasRegisterAssigned() && !current->spilled());
3798
3799 ProcessCurrentRange(current, spill_mode);
3800 }
3801
3802 if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_alloc) {
3803 PrintRangeOverview();
3804 }
3805}

3818void LinearScanAllocator::AddToActive(LiveRange* range) {
3819 TRACE("Add live range %d:%d in %s to active\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3820 range->relative_id(), RegisterName(range->assigned_register()));
3821 active_live_ranges().push_back(range);
3822 next_active_ranges_change_ =
3823 std::min(next_active_ranges_change_, range->NextEndAfter(range->Start()));
3824}

3826void LinearScanAllocator::AddToInactive(LiveRange* range) {
3827 TRACE("Add live range %d:%d to inactive\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3828 range->relative_id());
3829 next_inactive_ranges_change_ = std::min(
3830 next_inactive_ranges_change_, range->NextStartAfter(range->Start()));
3831 DCHECK(range->HasRegisterAssigned());
3832 // Keep `inactive_live_ranges` sorted.
3833 inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register())
3834 .insert(std::upper_bound(
3835 inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).begin(),
3836 inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).end(), range,
3837 InactiveLiveRangeOrdering()),
3838 1, range);
3839}

3843 DCHECK(!range->HasRegisterAssigned() && !range->spilled());
3844 DCHECK(allocation_finger_ <= range->Start());

3848 unhandled_live_ranges().insert(range);

3850
3851ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator LinearScanAllocator::ActiveToHandled(
3852 const ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator it) {
3853 TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from active to handled\n",
3854 (*it)->TopLevel()->vreg(), (*it)->relative_id());
3855 return active_live_ranges().erase(it);
3856}
3857
3858ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator LinearScanAllocator::ActiveToInactive(
3859 const ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator it, LifetimePosition position) {
3860 LiveRange* range = *it;
3861 TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from active to inactive\n",
3862 (range)->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
3863 LifetimePosition next_active = range->NextStartAfter(position);
3864 next_inactive_ranges_change_ =
3865 std::min(next_inactive_ranges_change_, next_active);
3866 DCHECK(range->HasRegisterAssigned());
3867 // Keep `inactive_live_ranges` sorted.
3868 inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register())
3869 .insert(std::upper_bound(
3870 inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).begin(),
3871 inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).end(), range,
3872 InactiveLiveRangeOrdering()),
3873 1, range);
3874 return active_live_ranges().erase(it);
3875}
3876
3877LinearScanAllocator::InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator
3878LinearScanAllocator::InactiveToHandled(InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator it) {
3879 LiveRange* range = *it;
3880 TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from inactive to handled\n",
3881 range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
3882 int reg = range->assigned_register();
3883 // This must keep the order of `inactive_live_ranges` intact since one of its
3884 // callers `SplitAndSpillIntersecting` relies on it being sorted.
3885 return inactive_live_ranges(reg).erase(it);
3886}
3887
3888LinearScanAllocator::InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator
3889LinearScanAllocator::InactiveToActive(InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator it,
3890 LifetimePosition position) {
3891 LiveRange* range = *it;
3892 active_live_ranges().push_back(range);
3893 TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from inactive to active\n",
3894 range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
3895 next_active_ranges_change_ =
3896 std::min(next_active_ranges_change_, range->NextEndAfter(position));
3897 int reg = range->assigned_register();
3898 // Remove the element without copying O(n) subsequent elements.
3899 // The order of `inactive_live_ranges` is established afterwards by sorting in
3900 // `ForwardStateTo`, which is the only caller.
3901 std::swap(*it, inactive_live_ranges(reg).back());
3902 inactive_live_ranges(reg).pop_back();
3903 return it;
3904}
3905
3906void LinearScanAllocator::ForwardStateTo(LifetimePosition position) {
3907 if (position >= next_active_ranges_change_) {
3908 next_active_ranges_change_ = LifetimePosition::MaxPosition();
3909 for (auto it = active_live_ranges().begin();
3910 it != active_live_ranges().end();) {
3911 LiveRange* cur_active = *it;
3912 if (cur_active->End() <= position) {
3913 it = ActiveToHandled(it);
3914 } else if (!cur_active->Covers(position)) {
3915 it = ActiveToInactive(it, position);
3916 } else {
3917 next_active_ranges_change_ = std::min(
3918 next_active_ranges_change_, cur_active->NextEndAfter(position));
3919 ++it;
3920 }
3921 }
3922 }
3923
3924 if (position >= next_inactive_ranges_change_) {
3925 next_inactive_ranges_change_ = LifetimePosition::MaxPosition();
3926 for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3927 for (auto it = inactive_live_ranges(reg).begin();
3928 it != inactive_live_ranges(reg).end();) {
3929 LiveRange* cur_inactive = *it;
3930 if (cur_inactive->End() <= position) {
3931 it = InactiveToHandled(it);
3932 } else if (cur_inactive->Covers(position)) {
3933 it = InactiveToActive(it, position);
3934 } else {
3935 next_inactive_ranges_change_ = std::min(
3936 next_inactive_ranges_change_,
3937 // This modifies `cur_inactive.next_start_` and thus
3938 // invalidates the ordering of `inactive_live_ranges(reg)`.
3939 cur_inactive->NextStartAfter(position));
3940 ++it;
3941 }
3942 }
3943 std::sort(inactive_live_ranges(reg).begin(),
3944 inactive_live_ranges(reg).end(), InactiveLiveRangeOrdering());
3945 }
3946 }
3947
3948 for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3949 SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(reg);
3950 }
3951}
3952
3953int LinearScanAllocator::LastDeferredInstructionIndex(InstructionBlock* start) {
3954 DCHECK(start->IsDeferred());
3955 RpoNumber last_block =
3956 RpoNumber::FromInt(code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1);
3957 while ((start->rpo_number() < last_block)) {
3958 InstructionBlock* next =
3959 code()->InstructionBlockAt(start->rpo_number().Next());
3960 if (!next->IsDeferred()) break;
3961 start = next;
3962 }
3963 return start->last_instruction_index();
3964}

3995
3996void LinearScanAllocator::FindFreeRegistersForRange(
3997 LiveRange* range, base::Vector<LifetimePosition> positions) {
3998 int num_regs = num_registers();
3999 int num_codes = num_allocatable_registers();
4000 const int* codes = allocatable_register_codes();
4001 MachineRepresentation rep = range->representation();
4002 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine &&
4003 (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32 ||
4004 rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4005 GetFPRegisterSet(rep, &num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4006 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent &&
4007 (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4008 GetSIMD128RegisterSet(&num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4009 }
4010 DCHECK_GE(positions.length(), num_regs);
4011
4012 for (int i = 0; i < num_regs; ++i) {
4013 positions[i] = LifetimePosition::MaxPosition();
4014 }
4015
4016 for (LiveRange* cur_active : active_live_ranges()) {
4017 int cur_reg = cur_active->assigned_register();
4018 if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4019 positions[cur_reg] = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4020 TRACE("Register %s is free until pos %d (1) due to %d\n",
4021 RegisterName(cur_reg),
4022 LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0).value(),
4023 cur_active->TopLevel()->vreg());
4024 } else {
4025 int alias_base_index = -1;
4026 int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4027 cur_active->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4028 DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4029 while (aliases--) {
4030 int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4031 positions[aliased_reg] = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4032 }
4033 }
4034 }
4035
4036 for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_regs; ++cur_reg) {
4037 SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
4038 for (LiveRange* cur_inactive : inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg)) {
4039 DCHECK_GT(cur_inactive->End(), range->Start());
4040 DCHECK_EQ(cur_inactive->assigned_register(), cur_reg);
4041 // No need to carry out intersections, when this register won't be
4042 // interesting to this range anyway.
4043 // TODO(mtrofin): extend to aliased ranges, too.
4044 if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) &&
4045 (positions[cur_reg] <= cur_inactive->NextStart() ||
4046 range->End() <= cur_inactive->NextStart())) {
4047 break;
4048 }
4049 LifetimePosition next_intersection =
4050 cur_inactive->FirstIntersection(range);
4051 if (!next_intersection.IsValid()) continue;
4052 if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4053 positions[cur_reg] = std::min(positions[cur_reg], next_intersection);
4054 TRACE("Register %s is free until pos %d (2)\n", RegisterName(cur_reg),
4055 positions[cur_reg].value());
4056 } else {
4057 int alias_base_index = -1;
4058 int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4059 cur_inactive->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4060 DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4061 while (aliases--) {
4062 int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4063 positions[aliased_reg] =
4064 std::min(positions[aliased_reg], next_intersection);
4065 }
4066 }
4067 }
4068 }
4069}
4070
4071// High-level register allocation summary:
4072//
4073// We attempt to first allocate the preferred (hint) register. If that is not
4074// possible, we find a register that's free, and allocate that. If that's not
4075// possible, we search for a register to steal from a range that was allocated.
4076// The goal is to optimize for throughput by avoiding register-to-memory moves,
4077// which are expensive.
4078void LinearScanAllocator::ProcessCurrentRange(LiveRange* current,
4079 SpillMode spill_mode) {
4080 base::EmbeddedVector<LifetimePosition, RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters>
4081 free_until_pos;
4082 FindFreeRegistersForRange(current, free_until_pos);
4083 if (!TryAllocatePreferredReg(current, free_until_pos)) {
4084 if (!TryAllocateFreeReg(current, free_until_pos)) {
4085 AllocateBlockedReg(current, spill_mode);
4086 }
4087 }
4088 if (current->HasRegisterAssigned()) {
4089 AddToActive(current);
4090 }
4091}
4092
4093bool LinearScanAllocator::TryAllocatePreferredReg(
4094 LiveRange* current, base::Vector<const LifetimePosition> free_until_pos) {
4095 int hint_register;
4096 if (current->RegisterFromControlFlow(&hint_register) ||
4097 current->RegisterFromFirstHint(&hint_register) ||
4098 current->RegisterFromBundle(&hint_register)) {
4099 TRACE(
4100 "Found reg hint %s (free until [%d) for live range %d:%d (end %d[).\n",
4101 RegisterName(hint_register), free_until_pos[hint_register].value(),
4102 current->TopLevel()->vreg(), current->relative_id(),
4103 current->End().value());
4104
4105 // The desired register is free until the end of the current live range.
4106 if (free_until_pos[hint_register] >= current->End()) {
4107 TRACE("Assigning preferred reg %s to live range %d:%d\n",
4108 RegisterName(hint_register), current->TopLevel()->vreg(),
4109 current->relative_id());
4110 SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(current, hint_register);
4111 return true;
4112 }
4113 }
4114 return false;
4115}
4116
4117int LinearScanAllocator::PickRegisterThatIsAvailableLongest(
4118 LiveRange* current, int hint_reg,
4119 base::Vector<const LifetimePosition> free_until_pos) {
4120 int num_regs = 0; // used only for the call to GetFPRegisterSet.
4121 int num_codes = num_allocatable_registers();
4122 const int* codes = allocatable_register_codes();
4123 MachineRepresentation rep = current->representation();
4124 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine &&
4125 (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32 ||
4126 rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4127 GetFPRegisterSet(rep, &num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4128 } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent &&
4129 (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4130 GetSIMD128RegisterSet(&num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4131 }
4132
4133 DCHECK_GE(free_until_pos.length(), num_codes);
4134
4135 // Find the register which stays free for the longest time. Check for
4136 // the hinted register first, as we might want to use that one. Only
4137 // count full instructions for free ranges, as an instruction's internal
4138 // positions do not help but might shadow a hinted register. This is
4139 // typically the case for function calls, where all registered are
4140 // cloberred after the call except for the argument registers, which are
4141 // set before the call. Hence, the argument registers always get ignored,
4142 // as their available time is shorter.
4143 int reg = (hint_reg == kUnassignedRegister) ? codes[0] : hint_reg;
4144 int current_free = free_until_pos[reg].ToInstructionIndex();
4145 for (int i = 0; i < num_codes; ++i) {
4146 int code = codes[i];
4147 // Prefer registers that have no fixed uses to avoid blocking later hints.
4148 // We use the first register that has no fixed uses to ensure we use
4149 // byte addressable registers in ia32 first.
4150 int candidate_free = free_until_pos[code].ToInstructionIndex();
4151 TRACE("Register %s in free until %d\n", RegisterName(code), candidate_free);
4152 if ((candidate_free > current_free) ||
4153 (candidate_free == current_free && reg != hint_reg &&
4154 (data()->HasFixedUse(current->representation(), reg) &&
4155 !data()->HasFixedUse(current->representation(), code)))) {
4156 reg = code;
4157 current_free = candidate_free;
4158 }
4159 }
4160
4161 return reg;
4162}
4163
4164bool LinearScanAllocator::TryAllocateFreeReg(
4165 LiveRange* current, base::Vector<const LifetimePosition> free_until_pos) {
4166 // Compute register hint, if such exists.
4167 int hint_reg = kUnassignedRegister;
4168 current->RegisterFromControlFlow(&hint_reg) ||
4169 current->RegisterFromFirstHint(&hint_reg) ||
4170 current->RegisterFromBundle(&hint_reg);
4171
4172 int reg =
4173 PickRegisterThatIsAvailableLongest(current, hint_reg, free_until_pos);
4174
4175 LifetimePosition pos = free_until_pos[reg];
4176
4177 if (pos <= current->Start()) {
4178 // All registers are blocked.
4179 return false;
4180 }
4181
4182 if (pos < current->End()) {
4183 // Register reg is available at the range start but becomes blocked before
4184 // the range end. Split current before the position where it becomes
4185 // blocked. Shift the split position to the last gap position. This is to
4186 // ensure that if a connecting move is needed, that move coincides with the
4187 // start of the range that it defines. See crbug.com/1182985.
4188 LifetimePosition gap_pos =
4189 pos.IsGapPosition() ? pos : pos.FullStart().End();
4190 if (gap_pos <= current->Start()) return false;
4191 LiveRange* tail = SplitRangeAt(current, gap_pos);
4192 AddToUnhandled(tail);
4193
4194 // Try to allocate preferred register once more.
4195 if (TryAllocatePreferredReg(current, free_until_pos)) return true;
4196 }
4197
4198 // Register reg is available at the range start and is free until the range
4199 // end.
4200 DCHECK_GE(pos, current->End());
4201 TRACE("Assigning free reg %s to live range %d:%d\n", RegisterName(reg),
4202 current->TopLevel()->vreg(), current->relative_id());
4203 SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(current, reg);
4204
4205 return true;
4206}
4207
4208void LinearScanAllocator::AllocateBlockedReg(LiveRange* current,
4209 SpillMode spill_mode) {
4210 UsePosition* register_use = current->NextRegisterPosition(current->Start());
4211 if (register_use == nullptr) {
4212 // There is no use in the current live range that requires a register.
4213 // We can just spill it.
4214 LiveRange* begin_spill = nullptr;
4215 LifetimePosition spill_pos = FindOptimalSpillingPos(
4216 current, current->Start(), spill_mode, &begin_spill);
4217 MaybeSpillPreviousRanges(begin_spill, spill_pos, current);
4218 Spill(current, spill_mode);
4219 return;
4220 }
4221
4222 MachineRepresentation rep = current->representation();
4223
4224 // use_pos keeps track of positions a register/alias is used at.
4225 // block_pos keeps track of positions where a register/alias is blocked
4226 // from.
4227 base::EmbeddedVector<LifetimePosition, RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters>
4228 use_pos(LifetimePosition::MaxPosition());
4229 base::EmbeddedVector<LifetimePosition, RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters>
4230 block_pos(LifetimePosition::MaxPosition());
4231
4232 for (LiveRange* range : active_live_ranges()) {
4233 int cur_reg = range->assigned_register();
4234 bool is_fixed_or_cant_spill =
4235 range->TopLevel()->IsFixed() || !range->CanBeSpilled(current->Start());
4236 if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4237 if (is_fixed_or_cant_spill) {
4238 block_pos[cur_reg] = use_pos[cur_reg] =
4239 LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4240 } else {
4241 DCHECK_NE(LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0),
4242 block_pos[cur_reg]);
4243 use_pos[cur_reg] =
4244 range->NextLifetimePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(current->Start());
4245 }
4246 } else {
4247 int alias_base_index = -1;
4248 int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4249 range->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4250 DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4251 while (aliases--) {
4252 int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4253 if (is_fixed_or_cant_spill) {
4254 block_pos[aliased_reg] = use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4255 LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4256 } else {
4257 use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4258 std::min(block_pos[aliased_reg],
4259 range->NextLifetimePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(
4260 current->Start()));
4261 }
4262 }
4263 }
4264 }
4265
4266 for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_registers(); ++cur_reg) {
4267 SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
4268 for (LiveRange* range : inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg)) {
4269 DCHECK(range->End() > current->Start());
4270 DCHECK_EQ(range->assigned_register(), cur_reg);
4271 bool is_fixed = range->TopLevel()->IsFixed();
4272
4273 // Don't perform costly intersections if they are guaranteed to not update
4274 // block_pos or use_pos.
4275 // TODO(mtrofin): extend to aliased ranges, too.
4276 if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing())) {
4277 DCHECK_LE(use_pos[cur_reg], block_pos[cur_reg]);
4278 if (block_pos[cur_reg] <= range->NextStart()) break;
4279 if (!is_fixed && use_pos[cur_reg] <= range->NextStart()) continue;
4280 }
4281
4282 LifetimePosition next_intersection = range->FirstIntersection(current);
4283 if (!next_intersection.IsValid()) continue;
4284
4285 if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4286 if (is_fixed) {
4287 block_pos[cur_reg] = std::min(block_pos[cur_reg], next_intersection);
4288 use_pos[cur_reg] = std::min(block_pos[cur_reg], use_pos[cur_reg]);
4289 } else {
4290 use_pos[cur_reg] = std::min(use_pos[cur_reg], next_intersection);
4291 }
4292 } else {
4293 int alias_base_index = -1;
4294 int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4295 range->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4296 DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4297 while (aliases--) {
4298 int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4299 if (is_fixed) {
4300 block_pos[aliased_reg] =
4301 std::min(block_pos[aliased_reg], next_intersection);
4302 use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4303 std::min(block_pos[aliased_reg], use_pos[aliased_reg]);
4304 } else {
4305 use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4306 std::min(use_pos[aliased_reg], next_intersection);
4307 }
4308 }
4309 }
4310 }
4311 }
4312
4313 // Compute register hint if it exists.
4314 int hint_reg = kUnassignedRegister;
4315 current->RegisterFromControlFlow(&hint_reg) ||
4316 register_use->HintRegister(&hint_reg) ||
4317 current->RegisterFromBundle(&hint_reg);
4318 int reg = PickRegisterThatIsAvailableLongest(current, hint_reg, use_pos);
4319
4320 if (use_pos[reg] < register_use->pos()) {
4321 // If there is a gap position before the next register use, we can
4322 // spill until there. The gap position will then fit the fill move.
4323 if (LifetimePosition::ExistsGapPositionBetween(current->Start(),
4324 register_use->pos())) {
4325 SpillBetween(current, current->Start(), register_use->pos(), spill_mode);
4326 return;
4327 }
4328 }
4329
4330 // When in deferred spilling mode avoid stealing registers beyond the current
4331 // deferred region. This is required as we otherwise might spill an inactive
4332 // range with a start outside of deferred code and that would not be reloaded.
4333 LifetimePosition new_end = current->End();
4334 if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
4335 InstructionBlock* deferred_block =
4336 code()->GetInstructionBlock(current->Start().ToInstructionIndex());
4337 new_end =
4338 std::min(new_end, LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
4339 LastDeferredInstructionIndex(deferred_block)));
4340 }
4341
4342 // We couldn't spill until the next register use. Split before the register
4343 // is blocked, if applicable.
4344 if (block_pos[reg] < new_end) {
4345 // Register becomes blocked before the current range end. Split before that
4346 // position.
4347 new_end = block_pos[reg].Start();
4348 }
4349
4350 // If there is no register available at all, we can only spill this range.
4351 // Happens for instance on entry to deferred code where registers might
4352 // become blocked yet we aim to reload ranges.
4353 if (new_end == current->Start()) {
4354 SpillBetween(current, new_end, register_use->pos(), spill_mode);
4355 return;
4356 }
4357
4358 // Split at the new end if we found one.
4359 if (new_end != current->End()) {
4360 LiveRange* tail = SplitBetween(current, current->Start(), new_end);
4361 AddToUnhandled(tail);
4362 }
4363
4364 // Register reg is not blocked for the whole range.
4365 DCHECK(block_pos[reg] >= current->End());
4366 TRACE("Assigning blocked reg %s to live range %d:%d\n", RegisterName(reg),
4367 current->TopLevel()->vreg(), current->relative_id());
4368 SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(current, reg);
4369
4370 // This register was not free. Thus we need to find and spill
4371 // parts of active and inactive live regions that use the same register
4372 // at the same lifetime positions as current.
4373 SplitAndSpillIntersecting(current, spill_mode);
4374}
4375
4376void LinearScanAllocator::SplitAndSpillIntersecting(LiveRange* current,
4377 SpillMode spill_mode) {
4378 DCHECK(current->HasRegisterAssigned());
4379 int reg = current->assigned_register();
4380 LifetimePosition split_pos = current->Start();
4381 for (auto it = active_live_ranges().begin();
4382 it != active_live_ranges().end();) {
4383 LiveRange* range = *it;
4384 if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4385 if (range->assigned_register() != reg) {
4386 ++it;
4387 continue;
4388 }
4389 } else {
4390 if (!data()->config()->AreAliases(current->representation(), reg,
4391 range->representation(),
4392 range->assigned_register())) {
4393 ++it;
4394 continue;
4395 }
4396 }
4397
4398 UsePosition* next_pos = range->NextRegisterPosition(current->Start());
4399 LiveRange* begin_spill = nullptr;
4400 LifetimePosition spill_pos =
4401 FindOptimalSpillingPos(range, split_pos, spill_mode, &begin_spill);
4402 MaybeSpillPreviousRanges(begin_spill, spill_pos, range);
4403 if (next_pos == nullptr) {
4404 SpillAfter(range, spill_pos, spill_mode);
4405 } else {
4406 // When spilling between spill_pos and next_pos ensure that the range
4407 // remains spilled at least until the start of the current live range.
4408 // This guarantees that we will not introduce new unhandled ranges that
4409 // start before the current range as this violates allocation invariants
4410 // and will lead to an inconsistent state of active and inactive
4411 // live-ranges: ranges are allocated in order of their start positions,
4412 // ranges are retired from active/inactive when the start of the
4413 // current live-range is larger than their end.
4414 DCHECK(LifetimePosition::ExistsGapPositionBetween(current->Start(),
4415 next_pos->pos()));
4416 SpillBetweenUntil(range, spill_pos, current->Start(), next_pos->pos(),
4417 spill_mode);
4418 }
4419 it = ActiveToHandled(it);
4420 }
4421
4422 for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_registers(); ++cur_reg) {
4423 if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4424 if (cur_reg != reg) continue;
4425 }
4426 SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
4427 for (auto it = inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg).begin();
4428 it != inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg).end();) {
4429 LiveRange* range = *it;
4430 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing() &&
4431 !data()->config()->AreAliases(current->representation(), reg,
4432 range->representation(), cur_reg)) {
4433 ++it;
4434 continue;
4435 }
4436 DCHECK(range->End() > current->Start());
4437 if (range->TopLevel()->IsFixed()) {
4438 ++it;
4439 continue;
4440 }
4441
4442 LifetimePosition next_intersection = range->FirstIntersection(current);
4443 if (next_intersection.IsValid()) {
4444 UsePosition* next_pos = range->NextRegisterPosition(current->Start());
4445 if (next_pos == nullptr) {
4446 SpillAfter(range, split_pos, spill_mode);
4447 } else {
4448 next_intersection = std::min(next_intersection, next_pos->pos());
4449 SpillBetween(range, split_pos, next_intersection, spill_mode);
4450 }
4451 it = InactiveToHandled(it);
4452 } else {
4453 ++it;
4454 }
4455 }
4456 }
4457}
4458
4459bool LinearScanAllocator::TryReuseSpillForPhi(TopLevelLiveRange* range) {
4460 if (!range->is_phi()) return false;
4461
4462 DCHECK(!range->HasSpillOperand());
4463 // Check how many operands belong to the same bundle as the output.
4464 LiveRangeBundle* out_bundle = range->get_bundle();
4465 RegisterAllocationData::PhiMapValue* phi_map_value =
4466 data()->GetPhiMapValueFor(range);
4467 const PhiInstruction* phi = phi_map_value->phi();
4468 const InstructionBlock* block = phi_map_value->block();
4469 // Count the number of spilled operands.
4470 size_t spilled_count = 0;
4471 for (size_t i = 0; i < phi->operands().size(); i++) {
4472 int op = phi->operands()[i];
4473 TopLevelLiveRange* op_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(op);
4474 if (!op_range->HasSpillRange() || op_range->get_bundle() != out_bundle)
4475 continue;
4476 const InstructionBlock* pred =
4477 code()->InstructionBlockAt(block->predecessors()[i]);
4478 LifetimePosition pred_end =
4479 LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
4480 pred->last_instruction_index());
4481 LiveRange* op_range_child = op_range->GetChildCovers(pred_end);
4482 if (op_range_child != nullptr && op_range_child->spilled()) {
4483 spilled_count++;
4484 }
4485 }
4486
4487 // Only continue if more than half of the operands are spilled to the same
4488 // slot (because part of same bundle).
4489 if (spilled_count * 2 <= phi->operands().size()) {
4490 return false;
4491 }
4492
4493 // If the range does not need register soon, spill it to the merged
4494 // spill range.
4495 LifetimePosition next_pos = range->Start();
4496 if (next_pos.IsGapPosition()) next_pos = next_pos.NextStart();
4497 UsePosition* pos = range->NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(next_pos);
4498 if (pos == nullptr) {
4499 Spill(range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
4500 return true;
4501 } else if (pos->pos() > range->Start().NextStart()) {
4502 SpillBetween(range, range->Start(), pos->pos(),
4503 SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
4504 return true;
4505 }
4506 return false;
4507}
4508
4509void LinearScanAllocator::SpillAfter(LiveRange* range, LifetimePosition pos,
4510 SpillMode spill_mode) {
4511 LiveRange* second_part = SplitRangeAt(range, pos);
4512 Spill(second_part, spill_mode);
4513}
4514
4515void LinearScanAllocator::SpillBetween(LiveRange* range, LifetimePosition start,
4516 LifetimePosition end,
4517 SpillMode spill_mode) {
4518 SpillBetweenUntil(range, start, start, end, spill_mode);
4519}
4520
4521void LinearScanAllocator::SpillBetweenUntil(LiveRange* range,
4522 LifetimePosition start,
4523 LifetimePosition until,
4524 LifetimePosition end,
4525 SpillMode spill_mode) {
4526 CHECK(start < end);
4527 LiveRange* second_part = SplitRangeAt(range, start);
4528
4529 if (second_part->Start() < end) {
4530 // The split result intersects with [start, end[.
4531 // Split it at position between ]start+1, end[, spill the middle part
4532 // and put the rest to unhandled.
4533
4534 // Make sure that the third part always starts after the start of the
4535 // second part, as that likely is the current position of the register
4536 // allocator and we cannot add ranges to unhandled that start before
4537 // the current position.
4538 LifetimePosition split_start = std::max(second_part->Start().End(), until);
4539
4540 // If end is an actual use (which it typically is) we have to split
4541 // so that there is a gap before so that we have space for moving the
4542 // value into its position.
4543 // However, if we have no choice, split right where asked.
4544 LifetimePosition third_part_end =
4545 std::max(split_start, end.PrevStart().End());
4546 // Instead of spliting right after or even before the block boundary,
4547 // split on the boumndary to avoid extra moves.
4548 if (data()->IsBlockBoundary(end.Start())) {
4549 third_part_end = std::max(split_start, end.Start());
4550 }
4551
4552 LiveRange* third_part =
4553 SplitBetween(second_part, split_start, third_part_end);
4554 if (GetInstructionBlock(data()->code(), second_part->Start())
4555 ->IsDeferred()) {
4556 // Try to use the same register as before.
4557 TRACE("Setting control flow hint for %d:%d to %s\n",
4558 third_part->TopLevel()->vreg(), third_part->relative_id(),
4559 RegisterName(range->controlflow_hint()));
4560 third_part->set_controlflow_hint(range->controlflow_hint());
4561 }
4562
4563 AddToUnhandled(third_part);
4564 // This can happen, even if we checked for start < end above, as we fiddle
4565 // with the end location. However, we are guaranteed to be after or at
4566 // until, so this is fine.
4567 if (third_part != second_part) {
4568 Spill(second_part, spill_mode);
4569 }
4570 } else {
4571 // The split result does not intersect with [start, end[.
4572 // Nothing to spill. Just put it to unhandled as whole.
4573 AddToUnhandled(second_part);
4574 }
4575}
4576
4577OperandAssigner::OperandAssigner(RegisterAllocationData* data) : data_(data) {}
4578
4579void OperandAssigner::DecideSpillingMode() {
4580 for (auto range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4581 data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4582 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4583 if (range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data())) {
4584 // If the range is spilled only in deferred blocks and starts in
4585 // a non-deferred block, we transition its representation here so
4586 // that the LiveRangeConnector processes them correctly. If,
4587 // however, they start in a deferred block, we uograde them to
4588 // spill at definition, as that definition is in a deferred block
4589 // anyway. While this is an optimization, the code in LiveRangeConnector
4590 // relies on it!
4591 if (GetInstructionBlock(data()->code(), range->Start())->IsDeferred()) {
4592 TRACE("Live range %d is spilled and alive in deferred code only\n",
4593 range->vreg());
4594 range->TransitionRangeToSpillAtDefinition();
4595 } else {
4596 TRACE("Live range %d is spilled deferred code only but alive outside\n",
4597 range->vreg());
4598 range->TransitionRangeToDeferredSpill(data()->allocation_zone());
4599 }
4600 }
4601 }
4602}
4603
4604void OperandAssigner::AssignSpillSlots() {
4605 ZoneVector<SpillRange*> spill_ranges(data()->allocation_zone());
4606 for (const TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4607 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4608 if (range->HasSpillRange()) {
4609 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range->GetSpillRange());
4610 spill_ranges.push_back(range->GetSpillRange());
4611 }
4612 }
4613 // At this point, the `SpillRange`s for all `TopLevelLiveRange`s should be
4614 // unique, since none have been merged yet.
4615 DCHECK_EQ(spill_ranges.size(),
4616 std::set(spill_ranges.begin(), spill_ranges.end()).size());
4617
4618 // Merge all `SpillRange`s that belong to the same `LiveRangeBundle`.
4619 for (const TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4620 data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4621 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4622 if (range->get_bundle() != nullptr) {
4623 range->get_bundle()->MergeSpillRangesAndClear();
4624 }
4625 }
4626
4627 // Now merge *all* disjoint, non-empty `SpillRange`s.
4628 // Formerly, this merging was O(n^2) in the number of `SpillRange`s, which
4629 // then dominated compile time (>40%) for some pathological cases,
4630 // e.g., https://crbug.com/v8/14133.
4631 // Now, we allow only `kMaxRetries` unsuccessful merges with directly
4632 // following `SpillRange`s. After each `kMaxRetries`, we exponentially
4633 // increase the stride, which limits the inner loop to O(log n) and thus
4634 // the overall merging to O(n * log n).
4635
4636 // The merging above may have left some `SpillRange`s empty, remove them.
4637 SpillRange** end_nonempty =
4638 std::remove_if(spill_ranges.begin(), spill_ranges.end(),
4639 [](const SpillRange* range) { return range->IsEmpty(); });
4640 for (SpillRange** range_it = spill_ranges.begin(); range_it < end_nonempty;
4641 ++range_it) {
4642 data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4643 SpillRange* range = *range_it;
4644 DCHECK(!range->IsEmpty());
4645 constexpr size_t kMaxRetries = 1000;
4646 size_t retries = kMaxRetries;
4647 size_t stride = 1;
4648 for (SpillRange** other_it = range_it + 1; other_it < end_nonempty;
4649 other_it += stride) {
4650 SpillRange* other = *other_it;
4651 DCHECK(!other->IsEmpty());
4652 if (range->TryMerge(other)) {
4653 DCHECK(other->IsEmpty());
4654 std::iter_swap(other_it, --end_nonempty);
4655 } else if (--retries == 0) {
4656 retries = kMaxRetries;
4657 stride *= 2;
4658 }
4659 }
4660 }
4661 spill_ranges.erase(end_nonempty, spill_ranges.end());
4662
4663 // Allocate slots for the merged spill ranges.
4664 for (SpillRange* range : spill_ranges) {
4665 data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4666 DCHECK(!range->IsEmpty());
4667 if (!range->HasSlot()) {
4668 // Allocate a new operand referring to the spill slot, aligned to the
4669 // operand size.
4670 int width = range->byte_width();
4671 int index = data()->frame()->AllocateSpillSlot(width, width);
4672 range->set_assigned_slot(index);
4673 }
4674 }
4675}
4676
4677void OperandAssigner::CommitAssignment() {
4678 const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
4679 for (TopLevelLiveRange* top_range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4680 data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4681 CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
4682 data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
4683 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(top_range);
4684 if (top_range->IsEmpty()) continue;
4685 InstructionOperand spill_operand;
4686 if (top_range->HasSpillOperand()) {
4687 auto it = data()->slot_for_const_range().find(top_range);
4688 if (it != data()->slot_for_const_range().end()) {
4689 spill_operand = *it->second;
4690 } else {
4691 spill_operand = *top_range->GetSpillOperand();
4692 }
4693 } else if (top_range->HasSpillRange()) {
4694 spill_operand = top_range->GetSpillRangeOperand();
4695 }
4696 if (top_range->is_phi()) {
4697 data()->GetPhiMapValueFor(top_range)->CommitAssignment(
4698 top_range->GetAssignedOperand());
4699 }
4700 for (LiveRange* range = top_range; range != nullptr;
4701 range = range->next()) {
4702 InstructionOperand assigned = range->GetAssignedOperand();
4703 DCHECK(!assigned.IsUnallocated());
4704 range->ConvertUsesToOperand(assigned, spill_operand);
4705 }
4706
4707 if (!spill_operand.IsInvalid()) {
4708 // If this top level range has a child spilled in a deferred block, we use
4709 // the range and control flow connection mechanism instead of spilling at
4710 // definition. Refer to the ConnectLiveRanges and ResolveControlFlow
4711 // phases. Normally, when we spill at definition, we do not insert a
4712 // connecting move when a successor child range is spilled - because the
4713 // spilled range picks up its value from the slot which was assigned at
4714 // definition. For ranges that are determined to spill only in deferred
4715 // blocks, we let ConnectLiveRanges and ResolveControlFlow find the blocks
4716 // where a spill operand is expected, and then finalize by inserting the
4717 // spills in the deferred blocks dominators.
4718 if (!top_range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) &&
4719 !top_range->HasGeneralSpillRange()) {
4720 // Spill at definition if the range isn't spilled in a way that will be
4721 // handled later.
4722 top_range->FilterSpillMoves(data(), spill_operand);
4723 top_range->CommitSpillMoves(data(), spill_operand);
4724 }
4725 }
4726 }
4727}

4729ReferenceMapPopulator::ReferenceMapPopulator(RegisterAllocationData* data)
4730 : data_(data) {}
4731
4732bool ReferenceMapPopulator::SafePointsAreInOrder() const {
4733 int safe_point = 0;
4734 for (ReferenceMap* map : *data()->code()->reference_maps()) {
4735 if (safe_point > map->instruction_position()) return false;
4736 safe_point = map->instruction_position();
4737 }
4738 return true;
4739}
4740
4741void ReferenceMapPopulator::PopulateReferenceMaps() {
4742 DCHECK(SafePointsAreInOrder());
4743 // Map all delayed references.
4744 for (RegisterAllocationData::DelayedReference& delayed_reference :
4745 data()->delayed_references()) {
4746 delayed_reference.map->RecordReference(
4747 AllocatedOperand::cast(*delayed_reference.operand));
4748 }
4749 // Iterate over all safe point positions and record a pointer
4750 // for all spilled live ranges at this point.
4751 int last_range_start = 0;
4752 const ReferenceMaps* reference_maps = data()->code()->reference_maps();
4753 ReferenceMaps::const_iterator first_it = reference_maps->begin();
4754 const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
4755 // Select subset of `TopLevelLiveRange`s to process, sort them by their start.
4756 ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*> candidate_ranges(data()->allocation_zone());
4757 candidate_ranges.reserve(data()->live_ranges().size());
4758 for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4759 CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
4760 data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
4761 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4762 // Skip non-reference values.
4763 if (!data()->code()->IsReference(range->vreg())) continue;
4764 // Skip empty live ranges.
4765 if (range->IsEmpty()) continue;
4766 if (range->has_preassigned_slot()) continue;
4767 candidate_ranges.push_back(range);
4768 }
4769 std::sort(candidate_ranges.begin(), candidate_ranges.end(),
4770 LiveRangeOrdering());
4771 for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : candidate_ranges) {
4772 // Find the extent of the range and its children.
4773 int start = range->Start().ToInstructionIndex();
4774 int end = range->Children().back()->End().ToInstructionIndex();
4775
4776 // Ranges should be sorted, so that the first reference map in the current
4777 // live range has to be after {first_it}.
4778 DCHECK_LE(last_range_start, start);
4779 last_range_start = start;
4780 USE(last_range_start);
4781
4782 // Step across all the safe points that are before the start of this range,
4783 // recording how far we step in order to save doing this for the next range.
4784 for (; first_it != reference_maps->end(); ++first_it) {
4785 ReferenceMap* map = *first_it;
4786 if (map->instruction_position() >= start) break;
4787 }
4788
4789 InstructionOperand spill_operand;
4790 if (((range->HasSpillOperand() &&
4791 !range->GetSpillOperand()->IsConstant()) ||
4792 range->HasSpillRange())) {
4793 if (range->HasSpillOperand()) {
4794 spill_operand = *range->GetSpillOperand();
4795 } else {
4796 spill_operand = range->GetSpillRangeOperand();
4797 }
4798 DCHECK(spill_operand.IsStackSlot());
4799 DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(
4800 AllocatedOperand::cast(spill_operand).representation()));
4801 }
4802
4803 LiveRange* cur = nullptr;
4804 // Step through the safe points to see whether they are in the range.
4805 for (auto it = first_it; it != reference_maps->end(); ++it) {
4806 ReferenceMap* map = *it;
4807 int safe_point = map->instruction_position();
4808
4809 // The safe points are sorted so we can stop searching here.
4810 if (safe_point - 1 > end) break;
4811
4812 // Advance to the next active range that covers the current
4813 // safe point position.
4814 LifetimePosition safe_point_pos =
4815 LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(safe_point);
4816
4817 // Search for the child range (cur) that covers safe_point_pos. If we
4818 // don't find it before the children pass safe_point_pos, keep cur at
4819 // the last child, because the next safe_point_pos may be covered by cur.
4820 // This may happen if cur has more than one interval, and the current
4821 // safe_point_pos is in between intervals.
4822 // For that reason, cur may be at most the last child.
4823 // Use binary search for the first iteration, then linear search after.
4824 bool found = false;
4825 if (cur == nullptr) {
4826 cur = range->GetChildCovers(safe_point_pos);
4827 found = cur != nullptr;
4828 } else {
4829 while (!found) {
4830 if (cur->Covers(safe_point_pos)) {
4831 found = true;
4832 } else {
4833 LiveRange* next = cur->next();
4834 if (next == nullptr || next->Start() > safe_point_pos) {
4835 break;
4836 }
4837 cur = next;
4838 }
4839 }
4840 }
4841
4842 if (!found) {
4843 continue;
4844 }
4845
4846 // Check if the live range is spilled and the safe point is after
4847 // the spill position.
4848 int spill_index = range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) ||
4849 range->LateSpillingSelected()
4850 ? cur->Start().ToInstructionIndex()
4851 : range->spill_start_index();
4852
4853 if (!spill_operand.IsInvalid() && safe_point >= spill_index) {
4854 TRACE("Pointer for range %d (spilled at %d) at safe point %d\n",
4855 range->vreg(), spill_index, safe_point);
4856 map->RecordReference(AllocatedOperand::cast(spill_operand));
4857 }
4858
4859 if (!cur->spilled()) {
4860 TRACE(
4861 "Pointer in register for range %d:%d (start at %d) "
4862 "at safe point %d\n",
4863 range->vreg(), cur->relative_id(), cur->Start().value(),
4864 safe_point);
4865 InstructionOperand operand = cur->GetAssignedOperand();
4866 DCHECK(!operand.IsStackSlot());
4867 DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(
4868 AllocatedOperand::cast(operand).representation()));
4869 map->RecordReference(AllocatedOperand::cast(operand));
4870 }
4871 }
4872 }
4873}

4876 : data_(data) {}

4878bool LiveRangeConnector::CanEagerlyResolveControlFlow(
4879 const InstructionBlock* block) const {
4880 if (block->PredecessorCount() != 1) return false;
4881 return block->predecessors()[0].IsNext(block->rpo_number());
4882}
4883
4884void LiveRangeConnector::ResolveControlFlow(Zone* local_zone) {
4885 ZoneVector<SparseBitVector*>& live_in_sets = data()->live_in_sets();
4886 for (const InstructionBlock* block : code()->instruction_blocks()) {
4887 if (CanEagerlyResolveControlFlow(block)) continue;
4888 SparseBitVector* live = live_in_sets[block->rpo_number().ToInt()];
4889 for (int vreg : *live) {
4890 data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4891 TopLevelLiveRange* live_range = data()->live_ranges()[vreg];
4892 LifetimePosition cur_start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
4893 block->first_instruction_index());
4894 LiveRange* cur_range = live_range->GetChildCovers(cur_start);
4895 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(cur_range);
4896 if (cur_range->spilled()) continue;
4897
4898 for (const RpoNumber& pred : block->predecessors()) {
4899 // Find ranges that may need to be connected.
4900 const InstructionBlock* pred_block = code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred);
4901 LifetimePosition pred_end =
4902 LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
4903 pred_block->last_instruction_index());
4904 // We don't need to perform the O(log n) search if we already know it
4905 // will be the same range.
4906 if (cur_range->CanCover(pred_end)) continue;
4907 LiveRange* pred_range = live_range->GetChildCovers(pred_end);
4908 // This search should always succeed because the `vreg` associated to
4909 // this `live_range` must be live out in all predecessor blocks.
4910 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(pred_range);
4911 // Since the `cur_range` did not cover `pred_end` earlier, the found
4912 // `pred_range` must be different.
4913 DCHECK_NE(cur_range, pred_range);
4914
4915 InstructionOperand pred_op = pred_range->GetAssignedOperand();
4916 InstructionOperand cur_op = cur_range->GetAssignedOperand();
4917 if (pred_op.Equals(cur_op)) continue;
4918
4919 if (!pred_op.IsAnyRegister() && cur_op.IsAnyRegister()) {
4920 // We're doing a reload.
4921 // We don't need to, if:
4922 // 1) there's no register use in this block, and
4923 // 2) the range ends before the block does, and
4924 // 3) we don't have a successor, or the successor is spilled.
4925 LifetimePosition block_start =
4926 LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(block->code_start());
4927 LifetimePosition block_end =
4928 LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(block->code_end());
4929 // Note that this is not the successor if we have control flow!
4930 // However, in the following condition, we only refer to it if it
4931 // begins in the current block, in which case we can safely declare it
4932 // to be the successor.
4933 const LiveRange* successor = cur_range->next();
4934 if (cur_range->End() < block_end &&
4935 (successor == nullptr || successor->spilled())) {
4936 // verify point 1: no register use. We can go to the end of the
4937 // range, since it's all within the block.
4938
4939 bool uses_reg = false;
4940 for (UsePosition* const* use_pos_it =
4941 cur_range->NextUsePosition(block_start);
4942 use_pos_it != cur_range->positions().end(); ++use_pos_it) {
4943 if ((*use_pos_it)->operand()->IsAnyRegister()) {
4944 uses_reg = true;
4945 break;
4946 }
4947 }
4948 if (!uses_reg) continue;
4949 }
4950 if (cur_range->TopLevel()->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) &&
4951 pred_block->IsDeferred()) {
4952 // The spill location should be defined in pred_block, so add
4953 // pred_block to the list of blocks requiring a spill operand.
4954 TRACE("Adding B%d to list of spill blocks for %d\n",
4955 pred_block->rpo_number().ToInt(),
4956 cur_range->TopLevel()->vreg());
4957 cur_range->TopLevel()
4958 ->GetListOfBlocksRequiringSpillOperands(data())
4959 ->Add(pred_block->rpo_number().ToInt());
4960 }
4961 }
4962 int move_loc = ResolveControlFlow(block, cur_op, pred_block, pred_op);
4963 USE(move_loc);
4964 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4965 cur_range->TopLevel()->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) &&
4966 !(pred_op.IsAnyRegister() && cur_op.IsAnyRegister()) &&
4967 move_loc != -1,
4968 code()->GetInstructionBlock(move_loc)->IsDeferred());
4969 }
4970 }
4971 }
4972
4973 // At this stage, we collected blocks needing a spill operand due to reloads
4974 // from ConnectRanges and from ResolveControlFlow. Time to commit the spills
4975 // for deferred blocks. This is a convenient time to commit spills for general
4976 // spill ranges also, because they need to use the LiveRangeFinder.
4977 const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
4978 SpillPlacer spill_placer(data(), local_zone);
4979 for (TopLevelLiveRange* top : data()->live_ranges()) {
4980 CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
4981 data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
4982 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(top);
4983 if (top->IsEmpty()) continue;
4984 if (top->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data())) {
4985 CommitSpillsInDeferredBlocks(top, local_zone);
4986 } else if (top->HasGeneralSpillRange()) {
4987 spill_placer.Add(top);
4988 }
4989 }
4990}
4991
4992int LiveRangeConnector::ResolveControlFlow(const InstructionBlock* block,
4993 const InstructionOperand& cur_op,
4994 const InstructionBlock* pred,
4995 const InstructionOperand& pred_op) {
4996 DCHECK(!pred_op.Equals(cur_op));
4997 int gap_index;
4998 Instruction::GapPosition position;
4999 if (block->PredecessorCount() == 1) {
5000 gap_index = block->first_instruction_index();
5001 position = Instruction::START;
5002 } else {
5003 Instruction* last = code()->InstructionAt(pred->last_instruction_index());
5004 // The connecting move might invalidate uses of the destination operand in
5005 // the deoptimization call. See crbug.com/v8/12218. Omitting the move is
5006 // safe since the deopt call exits the current code.
5007 if (last->IsDeoptimizeCall()) {
5008 return -1;
5009 }
5010 // In every other case the last instruction should not participate in
5011 // register allocation, or it could interfere with the connecting move.
5012 for (size_t i = 0; i < last->InputCount(); ++i) {
5013 DCHECK(last->InputAt(i)->IsImmediate());
5014 }
5015 DCHECK_EQ(1, pred->SuccessorCount());
5016 DCHECK(!code()
5017 ->InstructionAt(pred->last_instruction_index())
5018 ->HasReferenceMap());
5019 gap_index = pred->last_instruction_index();
5020 position = Instruction::END;
5021 }
5022 data()->AddGapMove(gap_index, position, pred_op, cur_op);
5023 return gap_index;
5024}
5025
5026void LiveRangeConnector::ConnectRanges(Zone* local_zone) {
5027 DelayedInsertionMap delayed_insertion_map(local_zone);
5028 const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
5029 for (TopLevelLiveRange* top_range : data()->live_ranges()) {
5030 CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
5031 data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
5032 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(top_range);
5033 bool connect_spilled = top_range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data());
5034 LiveRange* first_range = top_range;
5035 for (LiveRange *second_range = first_range->next(); second_range != nullptr;
5036 first_range = second_range, second_range = second_range->next()) {
5037 LifetimePosition pos = second_range->Start();
5038 // Add gap move if the two live ranges touch and there is no block
5039 // boundary.
5040 if (second_range->spilled()) continue;
5041 if (first_range->End() != pos) continue;
5042 if (data()->IsBlockBoundary(pos) &&
5043 !CanEagerlyResolveControlFlow(GetInstructionBlock(code(), pos))) {
5044 continue;
5045 }
5046 InstructionOperand prev_operand = first_range->GetAssignedOperand();
5047 InstructionOperand cur_operand = second_range->GetAssignedOperand();
5048 if (prev_operand.Equals(cur_operand)) continue;
5049 bool delay_insertion = false;
5050 Instruction::GapPosition gap_pos;
5051 int gap_index = pos.ToInstructionIndex();
5052 if (connect_spilled && !prev_operand.IsAnyRegister() &&
5053 cur_operand.IsAnyRegister()) {
5054 const InstructionBlock* block = code()->GetInstructionBlock(gap_index);
5055 DCHECK(block->IsDeferred());
5056 // Performing a reload in this block, meaning the spill operand must
5057 // be defined here.
5058 top_range->GetListOfBlocksRequiringSpillOperands(data())->Add(
5059 block->rpo_number().ToInt());
5060 }
5061
5062 if (pos.IsGapPosition()) {
5063 gap_pos = pos.IsStart() ? Instruction::START : Instruction::END;
5064 } else {
5065 if (pos.IsStart()) {
5066 delay_insertion = true;
5067 } else {
5068 gap_index++;
5069 }
5070 gap_pos = delay_insertion ? Instruction::END : Instruction::START;
5071 }
5072 // Reloads or spills for spilled in deferred blocks ranges must happen
5073 // only in deferred blocks.
5074 DCHECK_IMPLIES(connect_spilled && !(prev_operand.IsAnyRegister() &&
5075 cur_operand.IsAnyRegister()),
5076 code()->GetInstructionBlock(gap_index)->IsDeferred());
5077
5078 ParallelMove* move =
5079 code()->InstructionAt(gap_index)->GetOrCreateParallelMove(
5080 gap_pos, code_zone());
5081 if (!delay_insertion) {
5082 move->AddMove(prev_operand, cur_operand);
5083 } else {
5084 delayed_insertion_map.insert(
5085 std::make_pair(std::make_pair(move, prev_operand), cur_operand));
5086 }
5087 }
5088 }
5089 if (delayed_insertion_map.empty()) return;
5090 // Insert all the moves which should occur after the stored move.
5091 ZoneVector<MoveOperands*> to_insert(local_zone);
5092 ZoneVector<MoveOperands*> to_eliminate(local_zone);
5093 to_insert.reserve(4);
5094 to_eliminate.reserve(4);
5095 ParallelMove* moves = delayed_insertion_map.begin()->first.first;
5096 for (auto it = delayed_insertion_map.begin();; ++it) {
5097 bool done = it == delayed_insertion_map.end();
5098 if (done || it->first.first != moves) {
5099 // Commit the MoveOperands for current ParallelMove.
5100 for (MoveOperands* move : to_eliminate) {
5101 move->Eliminate();
5102 }
5103 for (MoveOperands* move : to_insert) {
5104 moves->push_back(move);
5105 }
5106 if (done) break;
5107 // Reset state.
5108 to_eliminate.clear();
5109 to_insert.clear();
5110 moves = it->first.first;
5111 }
5112 // Gather all MoveOperands for a single ParallelMove.
5113 MoveOperands* move =
5114 code_zone()->New<MoveOperands>(it->first.second, it->second);
5115 moves->PrepareInsertAfter(move, &to_eliminate);
5116 to_insert.push_back(move);
5117 }
5118}
5119
5120void LiveRangeConnector::CommitSpillsInDeferredBlocks(TopLevelLiveRange* range,
5121 Zone* temp_zone) {
5122 DCHECK(range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()));
5123 DCHECK(!range->spilled());
5124
5125 InstructionSequence* code = data()->code();
5126 InstructionOperand spill_operand = range->GetSpillRangeOperand();
5127
5128 TRACE("Live Range %d will be spilled only in deferred blocks.\n",
5129 range->vreg());
5130 // If we have ranges that aren't spilled but require the operand on the stack,
5131 // make sure we insert the spill.
5132 for (const LiveRange* child = range; child != nullptr;
5133 child = child->next()) {
5134 for (const UsePosition* pos : child->positions()) {
5135 if (pos->type() != UsePositionType::kRequiresSlot && !child->spilled())
5136 continue;
5137 range->AddBlockRequiringSpillOperand(
5138 code->GetInstructionBlock(pos->pos().ToInstructionIndex())
5139 ->rpo_number(),
5140 data());
5141 }
5142 }
5143
5144 ZoneQueue<int> worklist(temp_zone);
5145
5146 for (int block_id : *range->GetListOfBlocksRequiringSpillOperands(data())) {
5147 worklist.push(block_id);
5148 }
5149
5150 ZoneSet<std::pair<RpoNumber, int>> done_moves(temp_zone);
5151 // Seek the deferred blocks that dominate locations requiring spill operands,
5152 // and spill there. We only need to spill at the start of such blocks.
5153 SparseBitVector done_blocks(temp_zone);
5154 while (!worklist.empty()) {
5155 int block_id = worklist.front();
5156 worklist.pop();
5157 if (done_blocks.Contains(block_id)) continue;
5158 done_blocks.Add(block_id);
5159 InstructionBlock* spill_block =
5160 code->InstructionBlockAt(RpoNumber::FromInt(block_id));
5161
5162 for (const RpoNumber& pred : spill_block->predecessors()) {
5163 const InstructionBlock* pred_block = code->InstructionBlockAt(pred);
5164
5165 if (pred_block->IsDeferred()) {
5166 worklist.push(pred_block->rpo_number().ToInt());
5167 } else {
5168 LifetimePosition pred_end =
5169 LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
5170 pred_block->last_instruction_index());
5171
5172 LiveRange* child_range = range->GetChildCovers(pred_end);
5173 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(child_range);
5174
5175 InstructionOperand pred_op = child_range->GetAssignedOperand();
5176
5177 RpoNumber spill_block_number = spill_block->rpo_number();
5178 if (done_moves.find(std::make_pair(
5179 spill_block_number, range->vreg())) == done_moves.end()) {
5180 TRACE("Spilling deferred spill for range %d at B%d\n", range->vreg(),
5181 spill_block_number.ToInt());
5182 data()->AddGapMove(spill_block->first_instruction_index(),
5183 Instruction::GapPosition::START, pred_op,
5184 spill_operand);
5185 done_moves.insert(std::make_pair(spill_block_number, range->vreg()));
5186 spill_block->mark_needs_frame();
5187 }
5188 }
5189 }
5190 }
5191}
